{"term":"1956","caseName":"Holophane v. United States","caseLink":"https://www.oyez.org/cases/1956/2","caseTranscripts":[{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - November 05, 1956 (Part 1)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren4/oral_argument_audio/13174","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Number 2 on the docket, Holophane Company, Incorporated, Appellant, versus United States of America.","start":0,"stop":13.437,"duration":13.44},{"text":"Mr. Stevens.","start":13.437,"stop":16.163,"duration":2.73}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":16.163,"stop":20.177,"duration":4.01},{"text":"This case is a civil antitrust case originating in the Southern District of Ohio and tried before His Honor Mell G. Underwood.","start":20.177,"stop":35.027,"duration":14.85},{"text":"It comes before this Court upon appeal under the Expediting Act of 1903 from an order or judgment in decree entered by Judge Underwood February 8, 1954.","start":35.027,"stop":55.588,"duration":20.56},{"text":"A seasonable motion for new trial and other relief after judgment was filed and overruled February 9th, 1955.","start":55.588,"stop":68.833,"duration":13.24},{"text":"Thereafter, proceedings were perfected in this Court and jurisdiction noted October 10th, 1955.","start":68.833,"stop":79.072,"duration":10.24},{"text":"The complaint charged a violation of Section 1 of the Sherman Act by a reason of agreements existing between the appellant, which was the sole party defendant in this litigation and two foreign corporations.","start":79.072,"stop":108.773,"duration":29.7},{"text":"In other words, in general classification, this case is a cartel case.","start":108.773,"stop":117.702,"duration":8.93},{"text":"And yet I might say at the outset that if there ever was a case in which that word should not be endowed with talismanic qualities which preclude an examination under the rule of reason, this case is it.","start":117.702,"stop":138.908,"duration":21.21},{"text":"The appellant, Holophane Company, Inc. is a Delaware Corporation which has a factory in Newark, Ohio and its general offices in New York City.","start":138.908,"stop":161.04,"duration":22.13},{"text":"It manufactures prismatic glassware.","start":161.04,"stop":166.739,"duration":5.7},{"text":"That is glassware which is impressed with prismatic contours either in linear or circular form so arranged as to conduce to the projection of light patterns.","start":166.739,"stop":190.673,"duration":23.93},{"text":"I think on some of the exhibits Your Honors will see the slogan, “We turn light into illumination.”","start":190.673,"stop":200.871,"duration":10.2},{"text":"It is the function of this prismatic glassware to direct and focus or diffuse the light which comes from the source.","start":200.871,"stop":214.849,"duration":13.98},{"text":"The products include what are known as reflectors from which the light obviously bounces back, refractors through which the light passes and is bent into one direction or another, and lenses which perform in substance the same function as is performed by refractors.","start":214.849,"stop":245.749,"duration":30.9},{"text":"Generally speaking, refractors are used out of doors and lenses are used indoors.","start":245.749,"stop":255.251,"duration":9.5},{"text":"Refractors are a prominent element in the street lighting aspect of the Holophane business about which more will be stated later.","start":255.251,"stop":270.974,"duration":15.72},{"text":"Those are the physical products which Holophane makes.","start":270.974,"stop":276.094,"duration":5.12},{"text":"I might add that it not only makes the glass, but to some extent fabricates lighting fixtures which incorporate this prismatic glassware.","start":276.094,"stop":288.926,"duration":12.83},{"text":"It also sells prismatic glassware to other fabricators of lighting fixtures for incorporation by them in their own structures.","start":288.926,"stop":300.976,"duration":12.05},{"text":"Because of the oddity of the name, it might be worth just to comment upon that.","start":300.976,"stop":307.775,"duration":6.8},{"text":"The name, Holophane derives from two Greek combining forms holo, meaning complete, entire, or whole such as in holograph, holocaust and phane meaning to appear.","start":307.775,"stop":327.767,"duration":19.99},{"text":"And so the term in combination means wholly apparent or appearing completely.","start":327.767,"stop":336.248,"duration":8.48},{"text":"And I might say that I was delighted to find in the multivolume Oxford Dictionary last week that there actually is a word holophanerous meaning wholly apparent.","start":336.248,"stop":351.957,"duration":15.71},{"text":"The facts in this case as presented in the record below were developed by two witnesses who testified in person.","start":351.957,"stop":366.318,"duration":14.36},{"text":"One called upon cross-examination by the Government.","start":366.318,"stop":372.833,"duration":6.52},{"text":"The other adduced used by the appellant, the defendant below.","start":372.833,"stop":378.786,"duration":5.95},{"text":"Both were officers of the appellant.","start":378.786,"stop":382.492,"duration":3.71},{"text":"In addition, there are stipulations and numerous documents.","start":382.492,"stop":392.208,"duration":9.72},{"text":"The evidence shows in sum that the Holophane Industries as one might call them or industry stemmed from a meaning in 1892 between an American, Otis A. Mygatt, and a French man named Blondel.","start":392.208,"stop":416.04,"duration":23.83},{"text":"Professor Blondel had discovered the function performed by the impression of prisms on glassware in the focusing or diffusion of light.","start":416.04,"stop":429.21,"duration":13.17},{"text":"In 1898, Mr. Mygatt, the American, formed Holophane Glass Company of New Jersey and it proceeded to manufacture prismatic glassware.","start":429.21,"stop":443.475,"duration":14.27},{"text":"In 1912, Mr. Mygatt formed Holophane Limited, a British corporation.","start":443.475,"stop":457.793,"duration":14.32},{"text":"Some time between 1912 and 1921, Mr. Mygatt having become a resident of France formed La Societe Anonyme Francaise Holophane.","start":457.793,"stop":474.811,"duration":17.02},{"text":"He controlled not only Francaise and Limited, but also the American company which he made a fully own subsidiary of Limited.","start":474.811,"stop":488.619,"duration":13.81},{"text":"In 1921, there was in an agreement which appears in the record I believe Government's Exhibit 6 between Limited and Francaise in which Limited granted to Francaise the right or exclusive license to sell in a group of countries surrounding France, Belgium, Switzerland, Italy, Portugal, and Spain.","start":488.619,"stop":534.352,"duration":45.73},{"text":"By that agreement, Francaise was not to sell in British territory nor British to sell in French territory.","start":534.352,"stop":546.889,"duration":12.54},{"text":"That contract or agreement also provided that Limited was to have a representative on Francaise Board of Directors, with, of course, to have the right to inspect their books.","start":546.889,"stop":560.611,"duration":13.72},{"text":"Accountings were regularly to have been made and that the contract was to be construed as made under English law with the appointment of an agent for service of process in England.","start":560.611,"stop":577.429,"duration":16.82},{"text":"That was the situation which existed in 1925 when appellant's predecessor came into existence.","start":577.429,"stop":589.496,"duration":12.07},{"text":"Holophane Glass Company of New Jersey was, as I've indicated at that point a wholly owned subsidiary of Limited.","start":589.496,"stop":600.777,"duration":11.28},{"text":"The evidence shows that in 1925, the American management wished to acquire the American property for themselves that negotiations were conducted and a transaction consummated.","start":600.777,"stop":618.214,"duration":17.44},{"text":"That transaction in the record first evidences itself in an agreement between Limited and one Joel Liberman who was counsel for the American company and was associated with Mr. Charles Franck, then the American manager and now, president of Holophane Company, Incorporated, the appellant herein.","start":618.214,"stop":659.661,"duration":41.45},{"text":"Mr. Liberman has passed away.","start":659.661,"stop":663.203,"duration":3.54},{"text":"In that agreement, which was dated June 1st, 1925, Mr. Liberman acquired the opportunity or option to purchase the assets or the stock of the American company.","start":663.203,"stop":688.96,"duration":25.76},{"text":"It in that agreement, it was to be cited that there would be reciprocal recognition of trading areas.","start":688.96,"stop":700.569,"duration":11.61},{"text":"That agreement was assigned to a New York Corporation known as Holophane Illuminating Company which was formed along in September 25 and which exercised the option in the Liberman agreement so that in September of 1925, Holophane Illuminating Company, the New York corporation acquired from Limited whose negotiator was one Thompson, the General Manager of Limited acquired from it the stock of Holophane Glass Company, the New Jersey corporation.","start":700.569,"stop":750.97,"duration":50.4},{"text":"Immediately there was a change of name of the New York corporation to Holophane Glass Company.","start":750.97,"stop":757.624,"duration":6.65},{"text":"A year or so later, the name was changed to Holophane Company, Inc.","start":757.624,"stop":763.342,"duration":5.72},{"text":"In 1929, the New York corporation merged into a Delaware corporation which is the present appellant.","start":763.342,"stop":773.538,"duration":10.2},{"text":"In September --","start":773.538,"stop":777.491,"duration":3.95}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now who owns -- who owns the Delaware Corporation at the present time?","start":777.491,"stop":780.988,"duration":3.5},{"text":"Is that entirely independent?","start":780.988,"stop":782.574,"duration":1.59}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It's entirely independent --","start":782.574,"stop":783.578,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Independent.","start":783.578,"stop":784.104,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- Your Honor, yes.","start":784.104,"stop":784.62,"duration":0.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of Francaise and --","start":784.62,"stop":786.447,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It is.","start":786.447,"stop":787.103,"duration":0.66},{"text":"Thank you.","start":787.103,"stop":787.276,"duration":0.17}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":787.276,"stop":787.925,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"And I should state at that point that it is an interesting fact that in the acquisition of the American company by the American interests, Mr. Mygatt who, as I have said, originally controlled the entire enterprise owning Francaise, owning Limited, and initially owning the New Jersey corporation purchased all of the preferred shares of the American company, not common shares but the preferred shares and became president of the American Company.","start":787.925,"stop":834.65,"duration":46.73},{"text":"That is shown in the record by appropriate exhibits.","start":834.65,"stop":842.594,"duration":7.94},{"text":"At the present time, Holophane Company is, as I've indicated, entirely separate in ownership from Limited and Francaise.","start":842.594,"stop":853.694,"duration":11.1}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Is Mygatt -- he is not the president now.","start":853.694,"stop":856.152,"duration":2.46}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Mygatt is not the president.","start":856.152,"stop":856.346,"duration":0.19}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And did he have any of this --","start":856.346,"stop":857.929,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Mygatt -- Mygatt is -- Mygatt is dead.","start":857.929,"stop":858.513,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"-- first start?","start":858.513,"stop":860.581,"duration":2.07},{"text":"Has he evidence of the first start?(Voice Overlap) --","start":860.581,"stop":863.044,"duration":2.46}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) -- the record does not show that, Your Honor.","start":863.044,"stop":867.246,"duration":4.2}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Was that holding stock at all?","start":867.246,"stop":868.981,"duration":1.74}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It was not.","start":868.981,"stop":870.162,"duration":1.18},{"text":"The record does not show that without --","start":870.162,"stop":871.714,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"So, it was a passing phase that it wasn't --","start":871.714,"stop":873.412,"duration":1.7}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It was passing phase.","start":873.412,"stop":874.098,"duration":0.69}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)investment which is later was given up.","start":874.098,"stop":876.736,"duration":2.64}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I think thats correct, Your Honor.","start":876.736,"stop":879.129,"duration":2.39},{"text":"I think it is only fair to infer from that that in the financing of the purchase of the equity by the American management it was necessary for him to take preferred stock in order that the transaction will go forward.","start":879.129,"stop":897.741,"duration":18.61},{"text":"In September of 1925 a so-called trading agreement was entered into between the American company and Limited.","start":897.741,"stop":911.123,"duration":13.38},{"text":"That agreement which had been referred to in Mr. Liberman's original letter of -- to the company and said that a corresponding agreement might be offered with Francaise included territorial restrictions such that the American company was granted the right to sell Holophane products, all of these companies selling under the name of Holophane, all of them using the same trademark was given the right to sell Holophane products in that area of North America, north of the Panama Canal but exclusive of the West Indies, in Cuba and in Japan, and in the Philippine Islands.","start":911.123,"stop":969.941,"duration":58.82},{"text":"That agreement also provided that each party would use its best efforts to prevent exportation for its territory and to the territory of the other that each party would not carry on trade in the territory of the other.","start":969.941,"stop":987.887,"duration":17.95},{"text":"That each party will neither apply for nor obtain patent or trademark protection in the territory or countries of the other's territory without the request and -- but for the benefit of the other party.","start":987.887,"stop":1006.263,"duration":18.38},{"text":"That it will communicate and assign developments, discoveries, designs, and that it will supply the other when requested its products at factory cost plus 30%.","start":1006.263,"stop":1023.292,"duration":17.03},{"text":"Some few months later, the agreement which had been foreshadowed in Mr. Liberman's letter to the company along the same lines was consummated with Francaise and it was substantially the same sort of agreement.","start":1023.292,"stop":1040.488,"duration":17.2},{"text":"Along in 1944 after considerable correspondence and discussion between Limited and Francaise or rather Limited and the appellant about the South American rights to sell Holophane products, Limited granted the right to sell those products in South America to the American company, the appellant for some $40,300.","start":1040.488,"stop":1076.966,"duration":36.48},{"text":"At the same time, the agreement of September 15th, 1925, the trading agreement as I've called it, was renewed and it was designated that it would apply to the South American territory acquired by the American company.","start":1076.966,"stop":1101.844,"duration":24.88},{"text":"Interestingly enough, and in passing, both the original agreement between Mr. Liberman and Limited and the two agreements of 1944 which I have just mentioned, contained clauses which designate that the law of England shall apply and that a firm of solicitors shall be named, in fact, are named upon whom service of process can be made or any matter drawing out of the contract.","start":1101.844,"stop":1142.29,"duration":40.45},{"text":"In 1945, there was a further modification of the agreements which I have referred to, to take care of the percentages to be paid between Limited and the American company for certain additional work when one called upon the other to ship its goods into the territory of the other or when specification work was done by one company for shipment into the territory of the other.","start":1142.29,"stop":1176.897,"duration":34.61},{"text":"Now, in selling its prismatic glassware, Holophane Company, the appellant herein, in essence sells not a physical product but a service.","start":1176.897,"stop":1194.81,"duration":17.91},{"text":"The record is explicit on that subject note 5 on page 7 of the brief of the Government concedes that fact.","start":1194.81,"stop":1207.976,"duration":13.17},{"text":"That is, this is not a product which is sold in large by letter, by telephone but rather it is the result of an engineering service.","start":1207.976,"stop":1225.743,"duration":17.77},{"text":"A study is made by skilled lighting engineers who having perceived the problem, worked out a solution, make a recommendation and only when it is going through that process is the bulk of the business of this company transacted.","start":1225.743,"stop":1247.787,"duration":22.04},{"text":"The evidence shows that 75% of the total volume of Holophane business is done in that way.","start":1247.787,"stop":1257.841,"duration":10.05},{"text":"That there are 25 lighting engineers, sales engineers in its employ and that that is the normal course of business for this company.","start":1257.841,"stop":1272.878,"duration":15.04},{"text":"Now, the size of this company is an extremely interesting thing.","start":1272.878,"stop":1278.946,"duration":6.07},{"text":"As I have said, I believe, in 1925, it was acquired from Limited by the American Management Group for $1,000,000.","start":1278.946,"stop":1295.274,"duration":16.33},{"text":"Yet, in 1940, it had capital stock and surplus of 791,000.","start":1295.274,"stop":1304.8,"duration":9.53},{"text":"The highest reached shown in the record of this case, Your Honors is 1,859,000 in 1949 and in the year immediately prior to the filing of this suit, 1948, it had a total of capital stock and surplus of a 1,453,000.","start":1304.8,"stop":1328.835,"duration":24.04},{"text":"So it is apparent that this is a small company.","start":1328.835,"stop":1334.5,"duration":5.66},{"text":"Not only so because of the capital stock and surplus figures I had given but indeed because of the sales volume.","start":1334.5,"stop":1343.73,"duration":9.23},{"text":"Glassware sales in 1940 were 740,000.","start":1343.73,"stop":1349.744,"duration":6.01},{"text":"The high point shown in the record is 1951, when they ran 2,000,009.","start":1349.744,"stop":1357.056,"duration":7.31},{"text":"Total sales in 1940 were 1,111,000.","start":1357.056,"stop":1363.209,"duration":6.15},{"text":"Sales in 1951, the high point 4,678,000 and in the last year prior to the filing of this suit, some 2,091,000 in glassware and I think 1,000,425 in fixtures.","start":1363.209,"stop":1382.534,"duration":19.33}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Will these figures be a factor in your argument and (Voice Overlap) --","start":1382.534,"stop":1386.631,"duration":4.1}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"They will indeed.","start":1386.631,"stop":1386.912,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"On conditions that this is not a violation of the Act?","start":1386.912,"stop":1389.778,"duration":2.87}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"They will indeed, Your Honor.","start":1389.778,"stop":1393.828,"duration":4.05},{"text":"Now, on that background, it's interesting to see what competition this company has.","start":1393.828,"stop":1412.716,"duration":18.89},{"text":"Prismatic glassware, I have described, its competition, Your Honors, includes some nine companies in this country making products in prismatic glassware some of which this company does not make, many of which it does.","start":1412.716,"stop":1438.746,"duration":26.03},{"text":"Its competitors include such concerns as Corning Glass Works, one of the largest of the companies of its kind.","start":1438.746,"stop":1453.433,"duration":14.69}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you now referring to the competition within Continental America or competition dragging within its ambit restriction of territory both here and abroad?","start":1453.433,"stop":1467.513,"duration":14.08}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm referring to competition within this country.","start":1467.513,"stop":1471.056,"duration":3.54},{"text":"It also has as a competitor in this country, (Inaudible) which is even larger than Corning Glass Works.","start":1471.056,"stop":1483.084,"duration":12.03}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But the case ought to be, is it not, I'm asking, I don't know I must tell you is partly on the interrelation of what happens here or what happens abroad and the division of territory is that it?","start":1483.084,"stop":1493.518,"duration":10.43}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct, Your Honor.","start":1493.518,"stop":1494.62,"duration":1.1},{"text":"That's correct.","start":1494.62,"stop":1495.141,"duration":0.52}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"So that mere competition within the United States is being Holophane and A, B, C, D competitors isn't -- doesn't -- doesn't overlap.","start":1495.141,"stop":1507.194,"duration":12.05},{"text":"The problem is presented by the record in this case.","start":1507.194,"stop":1509.36,"duration":2.17}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It is not necessarily conclusive but we submit that it is the fact that's for consideration.","start":1509.36,"stop":1514.54,"duration":5.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Does it bear on the question of dividing territory?","start":1514.54,"stop":1517.962,"duration":3.42}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We think, Your Honor that -- that it does in this sense.","start":1517.962,"stop":1521.503,"duration":3.54},{"text":"That the record in this case shows that the only competition which has ever been affected is competition between or among the three Holophane companies that no competition outside or with outsiders has, in anyway, been affected.","start":1521.503,"stop":1546.05,"duration":24.55},{"text":"And that it is solely a matter of competition among those companies.","start":1546.05,"stop":1551.966,"duration":5.92},{"text":"Now, as I have said --","start":1551.966,"stop":1553.41,"duration":1.44}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's all independent companies which are also independent?","start":1553.41,"stop":1557.382,"duration":3.97}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Which are independent companies?","start":1557.382,"stop":1558.047,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Don't (Voice Overlap)","start":1558.047,"stop":1558.766,"duration":0.72}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, yes.","start":1558.766,"stop":1559.565,"duration":0.8},{"text":"Yes, it is.","start":1559.565,"stop":1559.82,"duration":0.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible) friendly relationship they are independent.","start":1559.82,"stop":1563.418,"duration":3.6}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"They are independent companies (Inaudible)","start":1563.418,"stop":1567.909,"duration":4.49}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Do your competitors give the same service that you do in the lighting service?","start":1567.909,"stop":1574.931,"duration":7.02}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it's my understanding that they are thoroughly competitive.","start":1574.931,"stop":1578.993,"duration":4.06},{"text":"I --","start":1578.993,"stop":1579.012,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Do they make the same kind of glass that you have?","start":1579.012,"stop":1581.438,"duration":2.43}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- it's my understanding they do.","start":1581.438,"stop":1582.984,"duration":1.55},{"text":"The record supports that.","start":1582.984,"stop":1589.462,"duration":6.48},{"text":"As to these agreements, I should say with the greatest candor that there is no doubt but what the appellant has lived up to them.","start":1589.462,"stop":1601.064,"duration":11.6},{"text":"As a matter of fact, counsel at trial told the Court that it was hardly necessary to examine the multitude of documents to determine that.","start":1601.064,"stop":1612.392,"duration":11.33},{"text":"That the appellant thought the agreements were legal to start with.","start":1612.392,"stop":1619.456,"duration":7.06},{"text":"Still thought they were legal and had adhered to them.","start":1619.456,"stop":1623.015,"duration":3.56},{"text":"And so, the fact is that we have carried out our end of the bargain which was entered into.","start":1623.015,"stop":1632.865,"duration":9.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there in the record anything that bears on that statement, namely, that this agreement was entered into, in the utmost good faith and if you please with -- to reasonably entertain legal views by counsel.","start":1632.865,"stop":1646.63,"duration":13.77},{"text":"The reason I ask that question is because for me at least that may bear somewhat on some aspect of the decree.","start":1646.63,"stop":1653.3,"duration":6.67}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well I think it does, Your Honor.","start":1653.3,"stop":1655.473,"duration":2.17},{"text":"I think the record does bear that out.","start":1655.473,"stop":1658.496,"duration":3.02},{"text":"I think that the record shows that, as I have said, the American management wished to buy the American company for itself.","start":1658.496,"stop":1671.224,"duration":12.73},{"text":"Mr. Mygatt controlled all of the companies.","start":1671.224,"stop":1675.736,"duration":4.51},{"text":"His manager of Limited, a man named Thompson, insisted that these provisions for an entry of appearance in England be it part of the contract.","start":1675.736,"stop":1696.632,"duration":20.9},{"text":"It is our submission on that subject that the American Holophane Company could never be -- have been born as an independent unit but for the acceptance of this territorial limitations anymore than if I undertake to borrow money from a bank I can get it without signing a cognovit note.","start":1696.632,"stop":1727.769,"duration":31.14},{"text":"That the same type of dominant compulsion which inserts the waiver and entry of appearance in a cognovit note existed here to compel that these gentlemen acquiring the American company agree to enter their appearance in any matter stemming from these contracts which might arise and enter it in England.","start":1727.769,"stop":1753.627,"duration":25.86},{"text":"And not only was that so, but the compulsion existed as long as 1944 when supplemental agreements were made.","start":1753.627,"stop":1764.011,"duration":10.38}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens, is this an appropriate time to ask you to give your explanation and answer to the opening statement of the Government in its summary of argument which it said in the court below appellant tried to impose findings of conclusions?","start":1764.011,"stop":1773.372,"duration":9.36}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll be very happy to, Your Honor, (Voice Overlap) --I was going to state that --","start":1773.372,"stop":1777.688,"duration":4.32}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"In addition of the markets among itself and Limited and Francaise are illegal and therefore not in the position to go ahead and --","start":1777.688,"stop":1782.726,"duration":5.04}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll be very happy to discuss that.","start":1782.726,"stop":1787.319,"duration":4.59},{"text":"When the facts had been presented to the Court as I have outlined -- now, Judge Underwood asked that counsel submit suggested or proposed findings of fact and conclusions of law and a proposed judgment and decree.","start":1787.319,"stop":1810.638,"duration":23.32},{"text":"That was done.","start":1810.638,"stop":1814.129,"duration":3.49},{"text":"The judgment and decree and the findings of fact and conclusions of law submitted by the appellant were submitted in this context.","start":1814.129,"stop":1828.669,"duration":14.54},{"text":"There had been discussion that Holophane Company wished to terminate this litigation.","start":1828.669,"stop":1839.461,"duration":10.79},{"text":"Counsel for the Government had been advised, Judge Underwood had been advised.","start":1839.461,"stop":1845.865,"duration":6.4},{"text":"It was apparent that at that time, 1953, the Timken decision having been made in 1951 being the latest, most thoroughly litigated decree in the field.","start":1845.865,"stop":1861.42,"duration":15.56},{"text":"That an irreducible minimum at which the appellant could hope to terminate this litigation was the general type of decree set forth or approved in the Timken case.","start":1861.42,"stop":1884.97,"duration":23.55},{"text":"And so in the proposed findings of fact and conclusions of law which the appellant gave to Judge Underwood it did have provisions which declared these contracts to be illegal and that is shown and discussed thoroughly, if the Court please, beginning on page 3 of the reply brief which we have filed.","start":1884.97,"stop":1920.28,"duration":35.31},{"text":"Just to set that matter in context and move on, my associate, Mr. Broad, seated at my left put it very colorfully.","start":1920.28,"stop":1933.157,"duration":12.88},{"text":"He said, at page 665 of the record, now on page 3 of my reply brief, \"My version of it is simply this.","start":1933.157,"stop":1943.146,"duration":9.99},{"text":"Feeling as strongly as we do that the agreements were essentially legal to begin with and perhaps are still legal, we can't afford the luxury of carrying on this expensive litigation which will put us out of business anyway.","start":1943.146,"stop":1958.794,"duration":15.65},{"text":"So we said to the Court and to the Government, very well we will concede the agreements are illegal.","start":1958.794,"stop":1965.687,"duration":6.89},{"text":"We will concede to the cancellation.","start":1965.687,"stop":1968.057,"duration":2.37},{"text":"We will concede never again, directly or indirectly, to be involved in any such agreements, but please leave us alone.\"","start":1968.057,"stop":1975.905,"duration":7.85},{"text":"The Government isn't content with that.","start":1975.905,"stop":1978.85,"duration":2.94},{"text":"It wants this little business out of Newark, Ohio to become a worldwide business.","start":1978.85,"stop":1983.993,"duration":5.14},{"text":"We haven't the capital, we haven't the manpower, we haven't the know-how to spread ourselves all over the world.","start":1983.993,"stop":1990.468,"duration":6.48},{"text":"And yet, if we are to comply with the decree that the Government submitted to Your Honor, we have one of these two desperate choices either to immediately cease doing business or to go broke within a year or two then we say that that's an imposition far beyond our means.","start":1990.468,"stop":2008.313,"duration":17.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens, does that generally too often broad refer to paragraph 8, 9, and 10 of the decree?","start":2008.313,"stop":2019.281,"duration":10.97},{"text":"Does that --","start":2019.281,"stop":2020.36,"duration":1.08}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It refer -- it refers, Your Honor to --","start":2020.36,"stop":2021.604,"duration":1.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- the Government to --","start":2021.604,"stop":2022.513,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- it refers --","start":2022.513,"stop":2022.697,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- get this --","start":2022.697,"stop":2023.122,"duration":0.43}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- Your Honor to the entire proposal which we made, which included the provisions under which the Court might then find illegality in the agreements about which we are concerned.","start":2023.122,"stop":2036.801,"duration":13.68}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, I understand that.","start":2036.801,"stop":2037.776,"duration":0.98},{"text":"But first statement, “the Government didn't contend with that.”","start":2037.776,"stop":2041.016,"duration":3.24}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, that's --","start":2041.016,"stop":2041.262,"duration":0.25}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You can leave us alone.","start":2041.262,"stop":2042.857,"duration":1.6},{"text":"Now, is that especially directed towards the --","start":2042.857,"stop":2044.922,"duration":2.07}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That -- that --","start":2044.922,"stop":2045.597,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- decree towards the duties enjoined upon you by the paragraph 8, 9, and 10 of the decree.","start":2045.597,"stop":2050.754,"duration":5.16}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2050.754,"stop":2051.512,"duration":0.76},{"text":"That specifically applies to portions of the decree which Mr. Broad colorfully described as (Inaudible).","start":2051.512,"stop":2059.262,"duration":7.75},{"text":"That is obliging this small American company to go abroad and perform affirmative acts abroad out of the jurisdiction of this country and in sovereignties where it does not have the protection of the decree which the District Court provided us.","start":2059.262,"stop":2079.981,"duration":20.72}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Provided the remarks with the decree which we have now before us -- before the Court in --","start":2079.981,"stop":2087.768,"duration":7.79}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Your Honor, this decree was subsequently added wherein --","start":2087.768,"stop":2091.399,"duration":3.63}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I know it wasn't obtained but was there already a submission by the Government --","start":2091.399,"stop":2096.503,"duration":5.1}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- there was.","start":2096.503,"stop":2096.859,"duration":0.36}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of a proposed decree of which this became formalized.","start":2096.859,"stop":2101.142,"duration":4.28}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Essentially so.","start":2101.142,"stop":2101.975,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":2101.975,"stop":2102.478,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Essentially so.","start":2102.478,"stop":2103.102,"duration":0.62}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And it was to that that this would be marked or addressed.","start":2103.102,"stop":2105.778,"duration":2.68}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Correct, Your Honor.","start":2105.778,"stop":2106.28,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Alright.","start":2106.28,"stop":2107.081,"duration":0.8}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens --","start":2107.081,"stop":2108.185,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, sir.","start":2108.185,"stop":2108.368,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"-- at that time and at this time you object to the language of a decree in the affirmative provisions in -- in the decree.","start":2108.368,"stop":2116.194,"duration":7.83}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":2116.194,"stop":2116.225,"duration":0.03}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"At that time, you were ready to yield on the legality point are you now?","start":2116.225,"stop":2120.832,"duration":4.61}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We're not, Your Honors.","start":2120.832,"stop":2122.189,"duration":1.36},{"text":"We're not.","start":2122.189,"stop":2123.316,"duration":1.13},{"text":"And we say we have neither waived nor conceded because the statements which were made in the proposals which were submitted to His Honor, Judge Underwood, were made in the context in which we were saying if this decree which we deemed to be in the form of the Timken decree applied to this case is accepted while we don't like it.","start":2123.316,"stop":2154.122,"duration":30.81},{"text":"We will take it and abide by it.","start":2154.122,"stop":2159.501,"duration":5.38}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"When the trial judge requested you to prepare your findings and proposed decree did he put it in that context or -- or did you put it in that context?","start":2159.501,"stop":2171.309,"duration":11.81}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I think it is fair to say I was not in the trial, Your Honor.","start":2171.309,"stop":2176.199,"duration":4.89},{"text":"I think it is fair to say that that was the context which existed at the time we were brought into the litigation.","start":2176.199,"stop":2184.449,"duration":8.25}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"By -- what do you mean yourself the person?","start":2184.449,"stop":2186.218,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I mean our office.","start":2186.218,"stop":2187.64,"duration":1.42}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, when what --","start":2187.64,"stop":2188.128,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"And that at that time, there was discussion between the Government and Holophane with the Court upon the basis upon which this whole thing might be terminated.","start":2188.128,"stop":2202.763,"duration":14.63},{"text":"And it is in that context that these submissions were made.","start":2202.763,"stop":2207.278,"duration":4.51}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there anything written by the Government or -- or stated by the judge in the record to the effect that the -- the -- one of the findings prepared in the -- in the light of some such understanding?","start":2207.278,"stop":2221.016,"duration":13.74}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"There is not, Your Honor.","start":2221.016,"stop":2222.344,"duration":1.33},{"text":"There is not.","start":2222.344,"stop":2223.076,"duration":0.73},{"text":"It's fair to state that.","start":2223.076,"stop":2225.417,"duration":2.34},{"text":"I -- I think when Your Honors examined however, the discussion of this subject in our reply brief, each will find that it is irrevocably documented that counsel for the Government understood that we were undertaking to work out in effect a final determination of the decree of the case at the trial court level by submission of what we considered to be a decree along the Timken lines.","start":2225.417,"stop":2258.002,"duration":32.59}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"But if you -- if you were wholly successful here or being in this Court, you would then have one of the competitors to deal with United States?","start":2258.002,"stop":2271.254,"duration":13.25}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We would have nine competitors.","start":2271.254,"stop":2274.085,"duration":2.83}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Well -- now are you speaking of those who are here now?","start":2274.085,"stop":2277.393,"duration":3.31}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Those who are here now.","start":2277.393,"stop":2278.216,"duration":0.82}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"To say one additional competitor or that would be the Cellophane -- Cellophane Company of France or --","start":2278.216,"stop":2287.789,"duration":9.57}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if we are successful in this case and the decree of Judge Underwood is set aside, then the contracts which have existed would still be in existence and neither process nor limited would export to this country.","start":2287.789,"stop":2319.636,"duration":31.85}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"And if you were not successful then you will --","start":2319.636,"stop":2321.715,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"If we weren't --","start":2321.715,"stop":2322.813,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"-- will open it to the --","start":2322.813,"stop":2324.364,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- we would -- we would open it to some degree to both limited and processed, correct.","start":2324.364,"stop":2331.312,"duration":6.95}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"But if you were successful, you wouldn't have to carry out other (Inaudible) would you compete with them --","start":2331.312,"stop":2338.183,"duration":6.87}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":2338.183,"stop":2338.918,"duration":0.74}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens, you are the best in the -- you will do your best how to use your time and speaking for myself, there are real problems about the decree and as I understand it --","start":2338.918,"stop":2348.841,"duration":9.92}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm -- I'm --","start":2348.841,"stop":2349.326,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- you only can go to 2 o'clock now if you get around the decree.","start":2349.326,"stop":2354.334,"duration":5.01}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm very interested.","start":2354.334,"stop":2355.82,"duration":1.49}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well , I know but it takes time.","start":2355.82,"stop":2357.647,"duration":1.83}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sure.","start":2357.647,"stop":2359.488,"duration":1.84},{"text":"Thank you.","start":2359.488,"stop":2362.286,"duration":2.8},{"text":"The decree which was ultimately entered by the Court, not only had a provision Section 5 which canceled these contracts and I suggest again that there was only one defendant before the Court, the American company, that Limited and Francaise were not before the Court.","start":2362.286,"stop":2387.86,"duration":25.57},{"text":"Not only cancel those contracts but ordered this company with $1,500,000 to $2,000,000 of networks.","start":2387.86,"stop":2402.04,"duration":14.18},{"text":"To perform affirmative acts abroad, we were directed in paragraph 11 set out in our brief, the principal brief pages 13 and 14, 15 to do specific things in paragraph (c) and then more broadly to use reasonable efforts including but not limited to the use of present or subsequent distributors or wholly owned subsidiaries.","start":2402.04,"stop":2432.443,"duration":30.4},{"text":"To promote the sale and the distribution of said products in foreign markets including the territories of Limited and Francaise.","start":2432.443,"stop":2441.552,"duration":9.11},{"text":"Now that, in substance, is the point which we are driving at.","start":2441.552,"stop":2449.196,"duration":7.64},{"text":"And on the background of facts which I have described, we have two large questions of law.","start":2449.196,"stop":2463.299,"duration":14.1},{"text":"We have one which is strictly an antitrust question.","start":2463.299,"stop":2470.662,"duration":7.36},{"text":"And that is, whether or not, the bare fact of territorial divisions and agreements existing between a company such as Holophane and foreign competitors makes that agreement per se illegal having in mind the size and market position of Holophane, having in mind the prior common ownership, and having in mind the fact that foreign commerce is involved.","start":2470.662,"stop":2518.535,"duration":47.87},{"text":"I set at the outset --","start":2518.535,"stop":2520.309,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now your point about common ownership, I don't get that.","start":2520.309,"stop":2522.939,"duration":2.63},{"text":"That doesn't exist where it's applied.","start":2522.939,"stop":2524.231,"duration":1.29}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- it does not exist but that point, Your Honor, is this.","start":2524.231,"stop":2530.868,"duration":6.64},{"text":"That if one takes a rule of reason approach rather than a flat per se test here, there is no way in which Holophane Company, the appellant, could have come in to existence but for the acceptance of the territorial limitations about which we are discussing.","start":2530.868,"stop":2560.946,"duration":30.08},{"text":"And in that context, in other words coming from the point of common ownership when obviously Limited would not sell and create a competitor, obviously Limited was bound to Francaise by its own agreements and couldn't create a competitor for Francaise.","start":2560.946,"stop":2583.284,"duration":22.34},{"text":"This company, if it came into existence, had to come into existence on that basis.","start":2583.284,"stop":2588.924,"duration":5.64},{"text":"I have said that this case among cartel cases is a refreshing one.","start":2588.924,"stop":2593.834,"duration":4.91},{"text":"We don't here have Your Honors the 100% control and domination of the nylon market for example such as existed in the Imperial Chemicals Du Pont case.","start":2593.834,"stop":2612.087,"duration":18.25},{"text":"We don't have here the 90% domination of the titanium market which we had in the National Lead case.","start":2612.087,"stop":2623.254,"duration":11.17},{"text":"We certainly don't have the 90% domestic market and the 80% non-domestic market which existed in (Inaudible), nor do we have the 70% to 80% domination of domestic market in Tapered Roller Bearings, and the 25% domination of added friction bearings at large which we had in the Timken case.","start":2623.254,"stop":2648.44,"duration":25.19},{"text":"Here we have a concern which sells prismatic glassware.","start":2648.44,"stop":2655.178,"duration":6.74},{"text":"Not a scrap of evidence was introduced to show the position of that concern in the prismatic glassware industry.","start":2655.178,"stop":2665.673,"duration":10.49},{"text":"Nothing suggests that it even remotely dominates it.","start":2665.673,"stop":2670.117,"duration":4.44},{"text":"In the complaint, there was an allegation that we had some 95% of the market in prismatic glassware for the street lighting industry, but the proof showed that the most we have is 3%.","start":2670.117,"stop":2688.47,"duration":18.35}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well this is -- your argument gets down to the proposition, this is only a little one.","start":2688.47,"stop":2692.333,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"This is only a little one among other things.","start":2692.333,"stop":2695.61,"duration":3.28}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But now assuming -- assuming that you, when you're on a decree, assuming that it's to be condemned under the Sherman law, what do you say about the decree and what's your objection?","start":2695.61,"stop":2704.746,"duration":9.14}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is the second large area of our discussion.","start":2704.746,"stop":2708.489,"duration":3.74},{"text":"We say first of all that there is not power in a District Court to order affirmative acts abroad.","start":2708.489,"stop":2719.519,"duration":11.03},{"text":"We say Your Honors that international law is intricately a part of our law.","start":2719.519,"stop":2728.147,"duration":8.63},{"text":"That one facet of international law forbids the intrusion by decree of this Court or the District Court into the affairs of other sovereignties.","start":2728.147,"stop":2744.571,"duration":16.42}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I had assumed that there's an actual or potential contradiction.","start":2744.571,"stop":2747.885,"duration":3.31}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That it does.","start":2747.885,"stop":2749.069,"duration":1.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Certainly the court of equity having the defendant report and make him do things and transfer land outside of the country.","start":2749.069,"stop":2755.081,"duration":6.01}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"There's no doubt about that but --","start":2755.081,"stop":2756.269,"duration":1.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, what is there -- what is there if the only escape clause in paragraph 11 acquires those?","start":2756.269,"stop":2764.46,"duration":8.19}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't believe there is an escape clause in paragraph 11.","start":2764.46,"stop":2768.21,"duration":3.75},{"text":"I don't think the word reasonable is an escape clause.","start":2768.21,"stop":2771.642,"duration":3.43},{"text":"I think we're talking as a matter of fact about power, Your Honor.","start":2771.642,"stop":2775.266,"duration":3.62}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No, but there's the sentence following your reasonable efforts then comes the clause nothing contained in this paragraph shall be construed in requiring the defendant to export any said products in violation of the valid transfer trademark of any foreign country.","start":2775.266,"stop":2790.725,"duration":15.46}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Because, Your Honor, that's only part of it.","start":2790.725,"stop":2793.763,"duration":3.04},{"text":"And the very language Your Honor has read indicates in part the fallacy of the decree below, because the Government was most circumspect in saying, “Oh, no, we will not intrude upon the patent or trademark law in the territory of Limited and Francaise.","start":2793.763,"stop":2816.251,"duration":22.49},{"text":"All we will do is violate fundamental contractual rights which exist there.”","start":2816.251,"stop":2822.273,"duration":6.02},{"text":"And we say that there are fundamental inviolable contractual rights recognizable under the law of England which exists in Limited and we believe recognizable under the law of France which exists in Francaise.","start":2822.273,"stop":2840.798,"duration":18.52}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you saying that this decree doesn't free you from subjection to an enforceable contract of English and French courts?","start":2840.798,"stop":2849.207,"duration":8.41},{"text":"Is that what you're saying?","start":2849.207,"stop":2849.756,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, that's in part.","start":2849.756,"stop":2850.845,"duration":1.09},{"text":"That's it.","start":2850.845,"stop":2851.665,"duration":0.82},{"text":"And we say that when we are obliged to go abroad, Your Honor, particularly in England where we already have an entry of appearance that the District Court has asked this company to expose itself in a foreign jurisdiction to a decree in a court of equity or a money judgment in a court of law.","start":2851.665,"stop":2877.884,"duration":26.22}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What would you say if the District Court requires you to go to an English court and get a declaration to its possibility of the form of the district contract and if you were to agree with the American court?","start":2877.884,"stop":2891.648,"duration":13.76}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say as a matter at bar the District Court had no right to do it.","start":2891.648,"stop":2896.03,"duration":4.38}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well it's asking you that this, the selling point is the filing of a violating of an American law.","start":2896.03,"stop":2904.69,"duration":8.66}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":2904.69,"stop":2905.338,"duration":0.65}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":2905.338,"stop":2906.318,"duration":0.98}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":2906.318,"stop":2906.985,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Therefore, to effectuate the violation you say that everything can be done but they didn't affect us generally.","start":2906.985,"stop":2915.478,"duration":8.49}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Within this country, yes.","start":2915.478,"stop":2917.33,"duration":1.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I don't think that's on the necessary limitation for the court of equity can make, it seems outside of it.","start":2917.33,"stop":2923.067,"duration":5.74}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"But the court of equity --","start":2923.067,"stop":2923.878,"duration":0.81}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The moment you don't collide potentially with the other countries.","start":2923.878,"stop":2927.069,"duration":3.19}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"And I'm submitting to Your Honor that you do collide with it that the British Nylon Spinners, Imperial Chemical Litigation, with which I know Your Honors are familiar demonstrates that you collide with it and that this Court in its opinion in Steelville, Bolivia and its Footnote 17 I believe --","start":2927.069,"stop":2947.263,"duration":20.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I --","start":2947.263,"stop":2947.662,"duration":0.4}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- so recognizes that as I --","start":2947.662,"stop":2949.302,"duration":1.64}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens --","start":2949.302,"stop":2949.665,"duration":0.36}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- believe Your Honor will know.","start":2949.665,"stop":2950.904,"duration":1.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens, I've suggested an alternative that doesn't appeal.","start":2950.904,"stop":2955.27,"duration":4.37},{"text":"And I hope the Government will address itself here to cull out the real problem in this case namely, not to make you include things (Inaudible) to make you go to the English court and say, “The American decree to which we are subject subjects us to the enforceability of the contract which for them is illegal but in this country it may not be illegal.","start":2955.27,"stop":2979.5,"duration":24.23},{"text":"We therefore ask a declaration from chancery that this -- that there is the jury and that we need to create it then, the impossibility of restoration, impossibility of performance, why shouldn't we be asked to go to the English court to get a declaration --","start":2979.5,"stop":2994.885,"duration":15.39}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I think --","start":2994.885,"stop":2995.387,"duration":0.5}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that will leave your responsibility for a contract on the English law with the American court where you should disregard it.","start":2995.387,"stop":3003.64,"duration":8.25}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- I think, Your Honor that we should not be asked to that.","start":3003.64,"stop":3007.322,"duration":3.68},{"text":"I think that the British law is plain that this -- that these contracts are valid.","start":3007.322,"stop":3012.986,"duration":5.66}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think you can say that British laws claim the right of the means (Inaudible)","start":3012.986,"stop":3018.463,"duration":5.48}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I respectfully suggest to Your Honor the British Monopolies Act does not touch this subject --","start":3018.463,"stop":3023.885,"duration":5.42}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'll have no power --","start":3023.885,"stop":3023.954,"duration":0.07}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and at this time to --","start":3023.954,"stop":3025.477,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I didn't say tag.","start":3025.477,"stop":3026.488,"duration":1.01},{"text":"I'm saying you didn't play.","start":3026.488,"stop":3027.948,"duration":1.46}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if I may proceed, I've to reserve my last one.","start":3027.948,"stop":3034.709,"duration":6.76}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Very well.","start":3034.709,"stop":3036.932,"duration":2.22},{"text":"Mr. Friedman.","start":3036.932,"stop":3038.87,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"May it please the Court.","start":3038.87,"stop":3039.895,"duration":1.03},{"text":"I would like first to discuss the question of violation and then the question of relief.","start":3039.895,"stop":3045.614,"duration":5.72},{"text":"On the question of violation, briefly touching on the question of the concession which the appellant made in the court below, we just want to point out that this case did not come before the District Court in the context of consent negotiations.","start":3045.614,"stop":3061.491,"duration":15.88},{"text":"This Court came before the District Court on a trial on the merits and after the trial had been completed, the District Judge directed both parties to file proposed findings and proposed conclusions.","start":3061.491,"stop":3072.531,"duration":11.04},{"text":"And the Government part had proposed findings and proposed conclusions in which it made various suggestions and concluded the violation of the Sherman Act had been shown.","start":3072.531,"stop":3082.274,"duration":9.74},{"text":"The appellant did not file a conclusion that a violation of the Sherman Act have not been shown on the contrary after the filing counter proposals on the facts, it then came along and filed a proposed conclusion of law that the agreements are illegal and further provided a proposed form of decree in it which is suggested that these agreements were -- should be cancelled and that where they had judged and adjudicated to be illegal in violation of the Sherman Act.","start":3082.274,"stop":3109.077,"duration":26.8}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Friedman, in this case were the Court's procedure followed that the abolishment (Inaudible) couldn't be a fair amount of cases with your, namely, the counsel first argued before the Court independently, that's up to divisions under the Sherman law and though they asked that judgments were granted on that -- on that issue of their illegal proceedings, it doesn't mean that the appropriate decree for the prior findings of the prior adjudication on the Sherman law.","start":3109.077,"stop":3139.131,"duration":30.05},{"text":"Or was it higgledy-piggledy (Inaudible)","start":3139.131,"stop":3142.205,"duration":3.07}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well it was, Your Honor, it was higgledy-piggledy but it was divided into two parts.","start":3142.205,"stop":3146.13,"duration":3.93},{"text":"There were two arguments before the District Court.","start":3146.13,"stop":3148.697,"duration":2.57},{"text":"There was first a trial on the merits but before the Court decided the case, the proposed findings, and proposed judgment was submitted.","start":3148.697,"stop":3157.828,"duration":9.13}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that but the plan and I have only the knowledge (Inaudible)","start":3157.828,"stop":3165.969,"duration":8.14},{"text":"The trial was concluded long before there was the argument before the judge handled it to the Court of which this colloquy took place.","start":3165.969,"stop":3173.79,"duration":7.82},{"text":"Is that right?","start":3173.79,"stop":3174.397,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct, Mr. Justice, but the --","start":3174.397,"stop":3175.809,"duration":1.41}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It wasn't exactly that these show that they knew the axe would fall or the axe had to fall on the religious (Inaudible) what kind of religion, what kind -- they knew what it was like.","start":3175.809,"stop":3186.716,"duration":10.91}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- they -- they didn't know that the axe had fallen but certainty they filed papers which suggested that they accepted the (Voice Overlap) --","start":3186.716,"stop":3193.613,"duration":6.9}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm saying that -- I'm saying they were stopped from making a decision.","start":3193.613,"stop":3198.738,"duration":5.13}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I hesitate to use the word stopped but I -- I say that --","start":3198.738,"stop":3201.609,"duration":2.87}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I commend you for that.","start":3201.609,"stop":3205.177,"duration":3.57}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"But, we -- we think it's -- it's rather odd after they make these concessions in the trial court for them to be now arguing before this Court as to the legality of the agreement.","start":3205.177,"stop":3216.741,"duration":11.56},{"text":"And that we're not questioning -- to question the decree because these concessions only went to the finding a violation of justice.","start":3216.741,"stop":3224.047,"duration":7.31}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is the proposal in the record of the -- of the side that asked the Court to find that their business was illegal?","start":3224.047,"stop":3235.98,"duration":11.93}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sorry, Mr. Justice.","start":3235.98,"stop":3237.482,"duration":1.5}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I understood you to say that they proposed in the findings of fact to the effect that they had been conducting the business in violation of the Sherman Act.","start":3237.482,"stop":3246.959,"duration":9.48}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Justice, that is --","start":3246.959,"stop":3247.564,"duration":0.61}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that?","start":3247.564,"stop":3248.479,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that is --","start":3248.479,"stop":3248.54,"duration":0.06}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where is that proposed?","start":3248.54,"stop":3249.421,"duration":0.88}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- record numbers -- page 648 which --","start":3249.421,"stop":3251.663,"duration":2.24}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3251.663,"stop":3251.686,"duration":0.02}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- is proposed conclusion of law number three.","start":3251.686,"stop":3256.358,"duration":4.67},{"text":"And then at Record 650 to 651, paragraph 4 of their proposed judgment beginning each of the following agreements is hereby declared and they judged it to be illegal.","start":3256.358,"stop":3268.428,"duration":12.07}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what was the other one?","start":3268.428,"stop":3269.676,"duration":1.25},{"text":"Six what?","start":3269.676,"stop":3270.526,"duration":0.85}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"650 and 651, Paragraph IV.","start":3270.526,"stop":3274.938,"duration":4.41}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's your judgment, you said.","start":3274.938,"stop":3277.437,"duration":2.5}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Mr. Justice.","start":3277.437,"stop":3278.411,"duration":0.97},{"text":"That is the defendant --","start":3278.411,"stop":3279.086,"duration":0.67}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3279.086,"stop":3279.666,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is their proposed judgment.","start":3279.666,"stop":3287.166,"duration":7.5}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"And that section to which you refer, they asked the Court to find.","start":3287.166,"stop":3294.247,"duration":7.08}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"They so --","start":3294.247,"stop":3294.976,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Did he find it was illegal?","start":3294.976,"stop":3296.743,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, he did, Mr. Justice.","start":3296.743,"stop":3298.72,"duration":1.98}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But don't you agree paragraph 3 with the preceding paragraph 2 under this lawyer documents (Inaudible) now, already to have you find it's fair?","start":3298.72,"stop":3311.189,"duration":12.47},{"text":"Is that fair?","start":3311.189,"stop":3312.421,"duration":1.23},{"text":"Is it one of those few?","start":3312.421,"stop":3314.352,"duration":1.93}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I think so, but I don't believe it -- that they proposed this in terms of saying, “We will concede the illegality of the agreements on condition --","start":3314.352,"stop":3327.107,"duration":12.76}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":3327.107,"stop":3327.22,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that the Court could not impose a decree greater than we proposed.","start":3327.22,"stop":3331.758,"duration":4.54}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"They were -- they've been glad that they thought of that and nothing else.","start":3331.758,"stop":3334.479,"duration":2.72}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It's not --","start":3334.479,"stop":3334.924,"duration":0.45}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well --","start":3334.924,"stop":3335.101,"duration":0.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"It's done.","start":3335.101,"stop":3336.065,"duration":0.96}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Was this proposed to the final judgment submitted just in the form of the news here without any discussion when they presented it to you in court?","start":3336.065,"stop":3347.278,"duration":11.21}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"This was submitted to the Court together with a subsequent brief and then there were hearings three months after these proposals had been filed of which they argued the question of what form of the judgment should be.","start":3347.278,"stop":3362.484,"duration":15.21}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm just trying to find out whether it was made in the in the form of a -- just a matter -- or whether it was made in a quick session, would that show from the brief that they filed, that we have brief here?","start":3362.484,"stop":3376.995,"duration":14.51}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It is not a part of the record, Mr. Justice.","start":3376.995,"stop":3379.881,"duration":2.89},{"text":"It could apply --","start":3379.881,"stop":3380.436,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But it was filed with the proposed final judgment.","start":3380.436,"stop":3384.191,"duration":3.75}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe so, Mr. Justice.","start":3384.191,"stop":3386.485,"duration":2.29}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Have you in mind whether or not that explained why they were submitting this?","start":3386.485,"stop":3390.849,"duration":4.36},{"text":"As for example that they did not concede the impropriety or the illegality of what they've been doing but they were willing to do -- to concede it to escape as I understood counsel for the expense was bearing on the litigation?","start":3390.849,"stop":3403.693,"duration":12.84}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I couldn't state that, Mr. Justice.","start":3403.693,"stop":3405.659,"duration":1.97},{"text":"They did so state at the subsequent hearings on the judgment.","start":3405.659,"stop":3412.094,"duration":6.43}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Where does that appear in the record?","start":3412.094,"stop":3413.753,"duration":1.66}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice.","start":3413.753,"stop":3414.86,"duration":1.11},{"text":"That's at 660 -- 665 it stated at one point and then began at 689.","start":3414.86,"stop":3446.809,"duration":31.95},{"text":"And turning now to the question of the legality of the agreements --","start":3446.809,"stop":3450.921,"duration":4.11}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Before you do that, would mind -- I hate to ask you?","start":3450.921,"stop":3454.59,"duration":3.67},{"text":"I would like to follow up.","start":3454.59,"stop":3455.529,"duration":0.94},{"text":"Do you say that the Court found that this was illegal that they requested.","start":3455.529,"stop":3459.393,"duration":3.86},{"text":"Where is that finding and conclusion and judgment?","start":3459.393,"stop":3471.131,"duration":11.74}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"The provision and the judgment, Mr. Justice Black, is at 695, paragraph 5.","start":3471.131,"stop":3481.317,"duration":10.19},{"text":"And the conclusion of law is at -- conclusion of law number 2 of Record 707-708 and then at Record 707, Findings 17, 18, 19, and 20, the Court found that the -- the agreements were illegal.","start":3481.317,"stop":3499.482,"duration":18.16}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What -- what's the last page?","start":3499.482,"stop":3501.179,"duration":1.7}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"707, Mr. Justice.","start":3501.179,"stop":3503.39,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, that reference which you gave on page 695 seemed -- refers to both contracts.","start":3503.39,"stop":3512.033,"duration":8.64},{"text":"Are the same contracts that were included in the request of findings that they were illegal at page 651?","start":3512.033,"stop":3521.404,"duration":9.37}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe so, Mr. Justice.","start":3521.404,"stop":3528.972,"duration":7.57},{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice, they're the same thing.","start":3528.972,"stop":3533.436,"duration":4.46},{"text":"Now, coming to the question of violation, that this Court repeatedly and consistently has condemned the agreements for the division of markets.","start":3533.436,"stop":3546.828,"duration":13.39},{"text":"It's condemned them in the foreign field.","start":3546.828,"stop":3548.649,"duration":1.82},{"text":"It's condemned them in the domestic field.","start":3548.649,"stop":3551.278,"duration":2.63},{"text":"And the amount of commerce involved has never been deemed significant.","start":3551.278,"stop":3556.387,"duration":5.11},{"text":"This is not a Section 2 case where we have to look to the definition of the relevant market.","start":3556.387,"stop":3562.387,"duration":6},{"text":"This is a Section 1 case involving agreements for the division of markets.","start":3562.387,"stop":3567.296,"duration":4.91},{"text":"And this Court --","start":3567.296,"stop":3567.427,"duration":0.13}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Friedman, may I interrupt just a moment before we get too far away from what we've just been discussing.","start":3567.427,"stop":3573.719,"duration":6.29},{"text":"You point out that paragraph 4 on page -- starts at the bottom of page 650 and going until 651 there are -- there are four contracts that are listed in -- in that proposal of the appellants.","start":3573.719,"stop":3591.557,"duration":17.84},{"text":"Then over on page 695, paragraph 5, the Court lists four other -- four contracts using the same language that -- that is used by the appellants but I noticed that the second one is dated 1925, September 15, 1925 between Holophane Glass Company and La Societe, et cetera, is dated September 15, 1925, (Inaudible) 695, it's dated September 15, 1923.","start":3591.557,"stop":3631.201,"duration":39.64},{"text":"Is that -- is that (Inaudible)?","start":3631.201,"stop":3632.748,"duration":1.55}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe so, Mr. Justice.","start":3632.748,"stop":3634.23,"duration":1.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"So, it should be -- they should be the same date?","start":3634.23,"stop":3636.502,"duration":2.27}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, because that is commonly referred to as the trading agreement --","start":3636.502,"stop":3640.068,"duration":3.57}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":3640.068,"stop":3641.005,"duration":0.94}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- agreement of September 15.","start":3641.005,"stop":3644.939,"duration":3.93},{"text":"I'm advised by Mr. Stevens that that date was corrected later on.","start":3644.939,"stop":3648.494,"duration":3.56},{"text":"I think it is a typographical error --","start":3648.494,"stop":3649.692,"duration":1.2}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm sure it was.","start":3649.692,"stop":3650.521,"duration":0.83}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- in the record.","start":3650.521,"stop":3651.081,"duration":0.56}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":3651.081,"stop":3657.419,"duration":6.34},{"text":"In the National Lead case and the Timken case this Court condemned agreements for the provision of markets.","start":3657.419,"stop":3664.794,"duration":7.38},{"text":"And I think it's significant that in the Timken case, as in this case, the agreements for the formation of the French company were entered into between the British company and the American company.","start":3664.794,"stop":3677.497,"duration":12.7},{"text":"So that the fact that you had -- had at the time of the execution of the agreements common control and common ownership of these company, does not save them from a concerned condemnation of the Sherman Act.","start":3677.497,"stop":3691.406,"duration":13.91},{"text":"Furthermore, there's nothing in this record to support the suggestion that if it hadn't been for these restricted provisions, the American company would never have been created.","start":3691.406,"stop":3705.938,"duration":14.53},{"text":"Some of the participants in this transaction were available as witnesses at the time of trial.","start":3705.938,"stop":3710.761,"duration":4.82},{"text":"They were not called.","start":3710.761,"stop":3712.188,"duration":1.43},{"text":"As far as the record in this case shows, we have an agreement for the sale of a portion of a business followed by an agreement not to compete, followed nine months later by an agreement not to compete with a third company that wasn't even a party to these negotiations.","start":3712.188,"stop":3731.096,"duration":18.91},{"text":"So we think that under the -- this Court's repeated holdings, these agreements are per se illegal.","start":3731.096,"stop":3738.641,"duration":7.55},{"text":"And we don't think that even if they were to be examined under the rule of reason, this can be justified as appellant seeks to do as an ancillary of strength.","start":3738.641,"stop":3748.767,"duration":10.13},{"text":"They're not limited in time, they're of indefinite duration, they're in existence at the time of the trial.","start":3748.767,"stop":3754.41,"duration":5.64},{"text":"They're not limited to territories where the companies were doing business, but broadly extended to the whole world.","start":3754.41,"stop":3760.39,"duration":5.98},{"text":"They contained numerous other restricted provisions going beyond merely staying out of the market areas, and finally, the agreements included a party which was not concerned directly with the transaction that's fair.","start":3760.39,"stop":3772.137,"duration":11.75}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Is it the Government's position, Mr. Friedman, that division of territory but getting on foreign, division of the territory is a violation per se (Inaudible)","start":3772.137,"stop":3785.736,"duration":13.6}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice.","start":3785.736,"stop":3786.513,"duration":0.78}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":3786.513,"stop":3787.791,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice.","start":3787.791,"stop":3789.874,"duration":2.08}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"We'll recess now.","start":3789.874,"stop":3794.098,"duration":4.22}]}]},{"transcriptTitle":"Oral Argument - November 05, 1956 (Part 2)","transcriptLink":"https://apps.oyez.org/player/#/warren4/oral_argument_audio/13336","transcript":[{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Referring to the question of violation, -- mention one of the brief matter, which is the Court's findings in this case on the fact of violation which is setout pages 706 to 707 of the record.","start":0,"stop":15.918,"duration":15.92},{"text":"And the Court there found that the defendant had failed to establish its contention that the agreements were subordinate to the alleged lawful -- unlawful purpose and it found on the contrary, they were designed to eliminate competition between the parties and were neither measurable by, limited to, nor subordinated to the reasonable necessities to the sale.","start":15.918,"stop":37.232,"duration":21.31},{"text":"So that wholly apart from the question of per se violation, the Court here found and we think clearly so that these agreements where unreasonable.","start":37.232,"stop":46.207,"duration":8.98},{"text":"And I now like to come to --","start":46.207,"stop":47.312,"duration":1.1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"The fact that it's legal findings show that did -- there -- there was estoppel or waiver or anything else to be followed?","start":47.312,"stop":54.355,"duration":7.04}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would assume not, Mr. Justice --","start":54.355,"stop":55.708,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"What?","start":55.708,"stop":56.44,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would assume not.","start":56.44,"stop":57.531,"duration":1.09}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":57.531,"stop":58.123,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"But --","start":58.123,"stop":60.829,"duration":2.71}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Would it be possible to establish that they were reasonable and necessary.Seemed so difficult to get evidence to that, on whether to give it a waive to that finding or not.","start":60.829,"stop":73.075,"duration":12.25}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I would say, Mr. Justice, that the way was open for the defendants to have introduced evidence to show he --","start":73.075,"stop":80.772,"duration":7.7}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"If the burden is on him to show that they were --","start":80.772,"stop":83.294,"duration":2.52}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"To show the facts --","start":83.294,"stop":84.024,"duration":0.73}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"-- reasonable and necessary.","start":84.024,"stop":85.019,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- relating to the execution of the agreements.","start":85.019,"stop":88.716,"duration":3.7},{"text":"And I would now like --","start":88.716,"stop":89.502,"duration":0.79}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"That suppose that your answer would be, that's irrelevant.","start":89.502,"stop":93.141,"duration":3.64}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is under the per se theory, Mr. Justice.","start":93.141,"stop":95.665,"duration":2.52},{"text":"But I was assuming --","start":95.665,"stop":96.698,"duration":1.03}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well --","start":96.698,"stop":97.033,"duration":0.34}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that they were not per se.","start":97.033,"stop":99.224,"duration":2.19},{"text":"On the --","start":99.224,"stop":99.462,"duration":0.24}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":99.462,"stop":103.66,"duration":4.2}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Never can tell what happens to you.","start":103.66,"stop":105.01,"duration":1.35},{"text":"[Laughs]","start":105.01,"stop":106.984,"duration":1.97}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Coming to what we think is the major question in this case, is the propriety of the provision and the decree directing the appellant to use reasonable efforts to promote the sale of its -- and distribution of its products and the territories, formerly allocated to the co-conspirators.","start":106.984,"stop":130.193,"duration":23.21},{"text":"We think that on the record in this case, there is nothing to show that there is any real likelihood or conflict between judgment of the American court, any possible judgments which may be entered by a foreign court.","start":130.193,"stop":148.996,"duration":18.8}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Would that be a permissible issue?","start":148.996,"stop":150.623,"duration":1.63},{"text":"Would you have to try English law before Judge Underwood --","start":150.623,"stop":154.909,"duration":4.29}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would believe so, Mr. Justice, where the contention is --","start":154.909,"stop":158.088,"duration":3.18}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- as to law?","start":158.088,"stop":159.506,"duration":1.42}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would believe so where the contention is made that the District Court should not direct these steps because the agreements are still valid under foreign law and there is -- his real likelihood of conflict.","start":159.506,"stop":175.233,"duration":15.73},{"text":"And of course, it's not only British and French law but it's the law of 20 or 30 different countries All these countries where they have stayed out, for example, Norway, Israel, Lebanon.","start":175.233,"stop":186.967,"duration":11.73},{"text":"All of these place.","start":186.967,"stop":187.887,"duration":0.92}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Can I take judicial notice for the English law for it precludes all division of territories?","start":187.887,"stop":192.246,"duration":4.36},{"text":"Or can I take also the contrary or do I have to be informed about that?","start":192.246,"stop":195.971,"duration":3.72}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would suggest, Mr. Justice that the third alternative is that information is necessary.","start":195.971,"stop":200.973,"duration":5},{"text":"I don't think that judicial notice can be taken in this field of law, particularly in English law, where there's change going on all the time.","start":200.973,"stop":207.965,"duration":6.99},{"text":"Now, we -- we're not suggesting before this Court that this agreements are clearly legal under English law.","start":207.965,"stop":214.494,"duration":6.53},{"text":"What we are suggesting is, that on the basis of what is before this Court, it cannot be said that the agreements are -- I'm sorry, I misspoke myself.","start":214.494,"stop":222.597,"duration":8.1},{"text":"We're not saying that the agreements are clearly legal under English law.","start":222.597,"stop":226.375,"duration":3.78},{"text":"All that we're saying is it cannot be assumed that the agreements are clearly illegal.","start":226.375,"stop":230.847,"duration":4.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And since this involved the activity in England, under a system of law which we know and by colloquy under the Sherman law, we know that much.","start":230.847,"stop":239.343,"duration":8.5}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":239.343,"stop":241.328,"duration":1.99}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Why isn't the burden on you to establish that?","start":241.328,"stop":245.992,"duration":4.66}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I think, Mr. Justice, because where the --","start":245.992,"stop":252.566,"duration":6.57}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You tell these people to go in there and actively beget competition.","start":252.566,"stop":257.163,"duration":4.6},{"text":"Is that right?","start":257.163,"stop":258.091,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if I may address myself to that as a threshold question.","start":258.091,"stop":262.741,"duration":4.65},{"text":"This decree merely directs them to use reasonable efforts.","start":262.741,"stop":267.226,"duration":4.49},{"text":"Now, we disagree with them that reasonable efforts means they have to send salesmen necessarily into England, that they have to do all of these things.","start":267.226,"stop":275.919,"duration":8.69},{"text":"We think there are many things which they can do without physically setting foot inside of England.","start":275.919,"stop":283.21,"duration":7.29},{"text":"For example, the question of advertising, the question of sending notice to the British Government, or the French Government that these products are now available, advising engineering, professional societies in that area.","start":283.21,"stop":297.103,"duration":13.89}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"This Court has said on more than one occasion about Sherman or decrees.","start":297.103,"stop":301.304,"duration":4.2},{"text":"They ought not to be indefinitely framed with all the threat of litigable contempt proceedings following it, is that right?","start":301.304,"stop":309.639,"duration":8.34}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice.","start":309.639,"stop":311.159,"duration":1.52}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you think we have to advertise?","start":311.159,"stop":313.388,"duration":2.23}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, that is specifically directed by --","start":313.388,"stop":317.116,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"You -- you tell him prominent, an advertising campaign, if the advertising campaign is -- was anything, well then, they've got to go ahead of me.","start":317.116,"stop":324.495,"duration":7.38}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the decree assumes that if they advertise and they get orders from these advertisements, they're going to fill them and send them abroad.","start":324.495,"stop":331.755,"duration":7.26}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Then they've got to find the capital some place and fill them.","start":331.755,"stop":336.009,"duration":4.25}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, we -- we assume that there's no contention made that they have to expand.","start":336.009,"stop":339.844,"duration":3.83},{"text":"They don't contend that they have to expand their production in order to fill these orders from abroad.","start":339.844,"stop":346.978,"duration":7.13}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"How can you say that you have allowed them?","start":346.978,"stop":349.824,"duration":2.85},{"text":"They shall within one year by a sentence as available, sufficient quantities of unmarked glass.","start":349.824,"stop":365.261,"duration":15.44}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, this may contemplate some expansion.","start":365.261,"stop":369.975,"duration":4.71},{"text":"This may contemplate the having availability -- available some unmarked glasses and glass with another trade mark, but there's nothing here to show that they'd have to, for example, build a new plant or something like that.","start":369.975,"stop":382.957,"duration":12.98}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, at least some money to that respect.","start":382.957,"stop":385.337,"duration":2.38}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I -- I would assume that.","start":385.337,"stop":386.834,"duration":1.5},{"text":"Yes, I think that inevitably, when you attempt to develop business in a new market, it's going to entail some cost.","start":386.834,"stop":393.438,"duration":6.6}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"That way, they must have good faith and try to develop the business.","start":393.438,"stop":396.277,"duration":2.84},{"text":"That way you --","start":396.277,"stop":397.271,"duration":0.99}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":397.271,"stop":399.531,"duration":2.26}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, Mr. Friedman, something more than the specific steps is contemplated, is it not?","start":399.531,"stop":404.527,"duration":5},{"text":"By reasonable efforts?","start":404.527,"stop":406.659,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I assume that -- we assume that reasonable efforts includes a specific steps, plus a little more.","start":406.659,"stop":415.287,"duration":8.63}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what's the little more?","start":415.287,"stop":416.512,"duration":1.23}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, such things as I have suggested which are not specifically spelled out.","start":416.512,"stop":421.001,"duration":4.49},{"text":"Such as -- what -- whatever steps they might feel reasonably would be required to try to develop the sales in this product, such as notifying possible purchases in the foreign country, notifying the Government --","start":421.001,"stop":434.057,"duration":13.06}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"But aren't -- aren't the notifications that you suggest embraced within the specific circularization required?","start":434.057,"stop":444.87,"duration":10.81}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We are suggesting that over and above, these are the specific circularizations, only to people who have requested an order who -- whose made an inquiry from the appellant, and the appellant has turned it down.","start":444.87,"stop":458.199,"duration":13.33}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"When I look at c (2), inserted advertisements.","start":458.199,"stop":464.223,"duration":6.02}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"In trade journal.","start":464.223,"stop":466.343,"duration":2.12}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, what other kind of advertisings affect the cost?","start":466.343,"stop":468.47,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, such as direct mail solicitation of other people, advising various trade societies and governmental groups in these territories.","start":468.47,"stop":481.045,"duration":12.57}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Should they join what passes for Chambers of Commerce in England and France?","start":481.045,"stop":484.719,"duration":3.67}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Pardon me, sir, I didn't hear it.","start":484.719,"stop":485.625,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Should they join what passes for Chambers of Commerce in England and France?","start":485.625,"stop":489.722,"duration":4.1}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, they -- they think this is necessary and reasonable to develop their business, the decree doesn't direct them to do that, at least a measure of flexibility to them.","start":489.722,"stop":499.281,"duration":9.56}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"How about warehouses?","start":499.281,"stop":501.087,"duration":1.81},{"text":"The storage of the products and those kinds?","start":501.087,"stop":505.328,"duration":4.24}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, there again, there's nothing to show that's it's necessary for them to warehouse the products.","start":505.328,"stop":509.581,"duration":4.25},{"text":"We assume that they can fill the orders from this country.","start":509.581,"stop":513.519,"duration":3.94},{"text":"Nothing in this record to show that it's necessary for them to warehouse products in those countries.","start":513.519,"stop":518.198,"duration":4.68}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"How about exhibits, affairs and things of that nature?","start":518.198,"stop":522.145,"duration":3.95}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if they fail that it -- it's appropriate for them to participate in these things, they -- certainly, I don't think there -- they would be held in contempt for not joining -- participating in the trade fair in London, say.","start":522.145,"stop":535.973,"duration":13.83}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the collection entails quite an expense, doesn't it?","start":535.973,"stop":540.763,"duration":4.79}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I think it -- it entail something of an expense but I think that there are provisions in antitrust decrees which entail considerable expense.","start":540.763,"stop":549.725,"duration":8.96},{"text":"And at the possible expense involved in complying with this decree has to be weighed on the other hand with the benefits which we think will result to the Commerce of the United States from this decree.","start":549.725,"stop":562.452,"duration":12.73},{"text":"I'd like to advert briefly to those benefits.","start":562.452,"stop":565.161,"duration":2.71}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"May I before you do that.","start":565.161,"stop":565.546,"duration":0.39}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Before you -- what's -- what is this, a penalty on them for their misconduct?","start":565.546,"stop":573.029,"duration":7.48}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Mr. Justice.","start":573.029,"stop":574.103,"duration":1.07},{"text":"This is designed to help pry oven -- open the avenues of competition which have been closed but --","start":574.103,"stop":580.666,"duration":6.56}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Where -- what -- what competition?","start":580.666,"stop":584.987,"duration":4.32}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"The fact that the foreign companies have never come into this country --","start":584.987,"stop":589.598,"duration":4.61}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"We're locked up to them, isn't it?You can't compel them to do that.","start":589.598,"stop":592.64,"duration":3.04}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, we can't but we help to stimulate them.","start":592.64,"stop":595.776,"duration":3.14}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"You mean by attacking them abroad, you stimulate them to come over here and fight this company?","start":595.776,"stop":601.036,"duration":5.26}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we hope.","start":601.036,"stop":601.807,"duration":0.77},{"text":"The hope is that the -- the theory of this decree is --","start":601.807,"stop":605.537,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But you don't mean that, do you?","start":605.537,"stop":607.843,"duration":2.31},{"text":"You don't meant that.","start":607.843,"stop":609.467,"duration":1.62},{"text":"That the -- one of the motives or one of the justifications for the decree is to stimulate foreign competition to come in the United States.","start":609.467,"stop":617.456,"duration":7.99},{"text":"That seems to me a new economic policy for an estoppel.","start":617.456,"stop":619.91,"duration":2.45}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, Mr. Justice.","start":619.91,"stop":620.963,"duration":1.05},{"text":"What I'm suggesting is that --","start":620.963,"stop":622.156,"duration":1.19}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I'm not saying it isn't desirable but the thing strikes me as not the kind of a thing that you could urge before most courts.","start":622.156,"stop":628.777,"duration":6.62}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we stop --","start":628.777,"stop":629.191,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"(Inaudible)","start":629.191,"stop":630.304,"duration":1.11}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, my -- my theory was directed at -- I'd understood that the purpose of a decree was to do away with the illegal actions that have taken place in this country and to restore competition if -- if there was other competition here.","start":630.304,"stop":648.476,"duration":18.17},{"text":"Now, you were directing this to the shift to other countries that are in the competition there.","start":648.476,"stop":655.322,"duration":6.85}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the --","start":655.322,"stop":656.346,"duration":1.02}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Bit -- and I just don't understand the purpose of that but --","start":656.346,"stop":658.246,"duration":1.9}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the restraints which we had in this case, our agreements under which the American company refuses to ship abroad and concomitantly, the foreign companies refuse to ship into this country.","start":658.246,"stop":672.616,"duration":14.37},{"text":"Now, the theory of the judge was that if you merely canceled the agreements, merely said, “These illegal agreements are canceled.”","start":672.616,"stop":680.964,"duration":8.35},{"text":"In view of this well-settled pattern that these companies had, this would not be enough to open up competition.","start":680.964,"stop":689.589,"duration":8.63},{"text":"They would be inclined to say the agreements have been canceled, we'll just go on about our way without the agreements.","start":689.589,"stop":695.696,"duration":6.11}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Were decrees suggested to the judge?","start":695.696,"stop":698.134,"duration":2.44}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, Mr. Justice.","start":698.134,"stop":699.485,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Did the Government suggested this decree?","start":699.485,"stop":701.256,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"The Government suggested this decree with one modification.","start":701.256,"stop":704.969,"duration":3.71},{"text":"The Government's proposed decree did not have the fist sentence in paragraph (11) A, the use of reasonable efforts.","start":704.969,"stop":712.948,"duration":7.98},{"text":"The judgment merely suggested the specific provisions set forth in paragraph c of (11).","start":712.948,"stop":722.059,"duration":9.11}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Freidman, under this decree, would it be open for the appellant to go before the Court and say, in view of the fact as that in full political parties that are going in for a high carat?","start":722.059,"stop":734.173,"duration":12.11},{"text":"We would seek our satisfactions by keeping the foreigners out and we don't want to engage in foreign practice, in foreign affairs.","start":734.173,"stop":742.27,"duration":8.1},{"text":"That they -- would -- would the Government cooperate with that condition --","start":742.27,"stop":745.166,"duration":2.9}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":745.166,"stop":745.284,"duration":0.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- or say, “No, he must fight in foreign market?","start":745.284,"stop":748.353,"duration":3.07}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, when we -- well, we certainly wouldn't cooperate in that position but I think --","start":748.353,"stop":752.954,"duration":4.6}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You'd oppose it, wouldn't you?","start":752.954,"stop":754.008,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right.","start":754.008,"stop":755.088,"duration":1.08},{"text":"Because I think the question of whether they have to go out in the abstract and do business abroad is not presented by this case.","start":755.088,"stop":764.681,"duration":9.59},{"text":"The question in this case is what they have to do when they have stayed out of the foreign markets as a result --","start":764.681,"stop":770.294,"duration":5.61}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"I understand that but they stayed out in part because they are protected against competition.","start":770.294,"stop":776.153,"duration":5.86},{"text":"Now, they say that you're in the judgment, they will get different barriers.","start":776.153,"stop":781.134,"duration":4.98},{"text":"They all erect different barriers against competition, namely, the -- they're not unfamiliar and not untraditional American territories.","start":781.134,"stop":790.104,"duration":8.97},{"text":"We don't want to go.","start":790.104,"stop":791.492,"duration":1.39},{"text":"There is the labor government on the horizon in England, and that will -- beget us difficulties, in various reasons, America is a big enough economic playground for us to cultivate.","start":791.492,"stop":803.504,"duration":12.01},{"text":"That this -- this decree says just the opposite, doesn't it?","start":803.504,"stop":808.584,"duration":5.08}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That's right because we think those are not proper considerations.","start":808.584,"stop":813.702,"duration":5.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"They are not for a business concern?","start":813.702,"stop":816.146,"duration":2.44}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Their proper considerations in determining where it wants to do business, certainly.","start":816.146,"stop":821.616,"duration":5.47},{"text":"But we don't have their proper considerations for the Court to take into account in determining whether it requires a company to take reasonable steps to compete abroad.","start":821.616,"stop":832.667,"duration":11.05}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But what is it the Court's business whether they should compete abroad or not so long as you throw off the shuttle against their restrictions to do so, their self-imposed restrictions.","start":832.667,"stop":842.332,"duration":9.66}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Because, Mr. Justice, the Court felt that the self-imposed restrictions, merely removing those, would not be enough to stimulate the American Foreign Commerce which has been a restrained by this conspiracy.","start":842.332,"stop":855.848,"duration":13.52}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Freidman, does this -- does this decree go any farther than to -- to require the appellants to give notice in other countries through the -- in -- in the trade to the effect that its policy is changed and that it is now willing to do business with them if they want to do business with this company.","start":855.848,"stop":881.774,"duration":25.93},{"text":"And that -- and requiring them to maintain themselves in the positions so far as their product is concerned to supply it if those people wan it.","start":881.774,"stop":892.776,"duration":11},{"text":"Now, does it move farther than that?","start":892.776,"stop":895.27,"duration":2.49}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say that it goes a little bit further than that.","start":895.27,"stop":897.682,"duration":2.41}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"And how much?","start":897.682,"stop":898.928,"duration":1.25},{"text":"That's what I'm asking you.","start":898.928,"stop":899.592,"duration":0.66},{"text":"[Laughter]","start":899.592,"stop":901.27,"duration":1.68}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say it's required them to give notice and also to make efforts to try to develop that trade to stimulate it.","start":901.27,"stop":910.109,"duration":8.84},{"text":"Now, the question as to how far they have to go to stimulate whether particular things might be done.","start":910.109,"stop":920.714,"duration":10.61},{"text":"That, it seems to us, comes within the broad area of business judgment.","start":920.714,"stop":927.056,"duration":6.34}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose for example -- now, the company were to say, “We can't manufacture in America and ship to France and England, our product and tries that competitively was a British and French product.","start":927.056,"stop":941.856,"duration":14.8},{"text":"Are they, nevertheless, to go through all this advertising and a little more that this suggest but to me at least, you haven't defined.","start":941.856,"stop":953.067,"duration":11.21},{"text":"In that circumstance, are they required to do all these?","start":953.067,"stop":955.281,"duration":2.21}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I don't think so, and I would suggest, Mr. Justice, in most circumstances, the appropriate procedure for them would be to go back to the District Court and either ask for modification or for a construction of the decree, that under the showing which they make, taking reasonable efforts did not require those steps.","start":955.281,"stop":975.018,"duration":19.74}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what they're doing now.","start":975.018,"stop":976.831,"duration":1.81}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I don't think so, Mr. Justice, because their contentions are predicated on no factual basis.","start":976.831,"stop":985.354,"duration":8.52},{"text":"The -- they just make these statements.","start":985.354,"stop":986.943,"duration":1.59},{"text":"They say that the agreements, for example, are clearly valid under foreign law.","start":986.943,"stop":992.749,"duration":5.81},{"text":"That is not established.","start":992.749,"stop":994.443,"duration":1.69},{"text":"They suggest --","start":994.443,"stop":995.356,"duration":0.91}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I suppose that is true, where whether they stand or they're valid under foreign law.","start":995.356,"stop":999.296,"duration":3.94}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"If they're valid under foreign law, that still does not necessarily mean that a foreign court would enter a judgment which would enjoin them from reaching the agreements there.","start":999.296,"stop":1010.284,"duration":10.99},{"text":"And the first --","start":1010.284,"stop":1010.507,"duration":0.22}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose they were valid over there to the extent that a man who was bought this felon could set up as defense, he didn't have to pay him and those are contracts (Inaudible) what would be the offense?","start":1010.507,"stop":1022.708,"duration":12.2},{"text":"Do they have take and jeopardize their judgments on him?","start":1022.708,"stop":1025.612,"duration":2.9}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think, Mr. Justice, they could protect themselves against that.","start":1025.612,"stop":1029.347,"duration":3.73}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"By getting cash?","start":1029.347,"stop":1030.492,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"By getting cash, by selling the goods FOB New York or wherever they ship from.","start":1030.492,"stop":1035.14,"duration":4.65}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, if they -- if they have any business over there, they could -- the Government could go after him if it's illegal.","start":1035.14,"stop":1041.111,"duration":5.97},{"text":"I think you have to meet that.","start":1041.111,"stop":1042.969,"duration":1.86}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well --","start":1042.969,"stop":1043.289,"duration":0.32}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"It would be the same, wouldn't it as though you -- an injunction under those circumstances were mandatory injunction for full-sale liquor business somewhere to do business in a State where there's -- against a law to sell liquor at all.","start":1043.289,"stop":1057.568,"duration":14.28}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we don't construe this judgment as requiring him to do anything which is illegal under foreign law in the sense that a foreign law provides a penalty for it.","start":1057.568,"stop":1068.208,"duration":10.64},{"text":"If there's any foreign ordinance or decree, which prohibits it, or if a foreign court enjoins them from -- before carrying on business in this countries.","start":1068.208,"stop":1078.634,"duration":10.43},{"text":"We think the direction to use reasonable efforts does not -- obviously, does not require that they violate the judgment of a foreign court.","start":1078.634,"stop":1085.733,"duration":7.1}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But it does leave open the fact that the English court may hold to say guilty of a breach of contract and the decree of Judge Underwood is no defense.","start":1085.733,"stop":1094.954,"duration":9.22},{"text":"That's nothing new.","start":1094.954,"stop":1095.904,"duration":0.95},{"text":"We've had this in experience in the English courts, vis-à-vis Judge Ryan's decree.","start":1095.904,"stop":1099.729,"duration":3.83}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That the Court may still hold, we don't know.","start":1099.729,"stop":1102.845,"duration":3.12}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But if --","start":1102.845,"stop":1103.864,"duration":1.02}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Court -- the courts may state that the type of disruption with contractual rights here involved is significantly different from that in the Nylon Spinners case.","start":1103.864,"stop":1115.669,"duration":11.81},{"text":"In the Nylon Spinners case, what they did was they directed them to reassign patents that had been assigned.","start":1115.669,"stop":1122.328,"duration":6.66},{"text":"Here, the only thing involved is a contractual, an executory contract not to do business there.","start":1122.328,"stop":1127.801,"duration":5.47}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, its -- doesn't -- unless my lawyer is awfully arrested here, that well may be but it doesn't go beyond my legal imagination as an English court may hold that this contract is valid.","start":1127.801,"stop":1138.701,"duration":10.9}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"It may well but the mere fact that the English court holds that this contract is valid --","start":1138.701,"stop":1143.679,"duration":4.98}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"And therefore, subjects the appellant to a breach of -- to a suit for breach of contract.","start":1143.679,"stop":1151.357,"duration":7.68},{"text":"If it behold it then it may enforce it in the way which breaching a contract are enforced.","start":1151.357,"stop":1158.848,"duration":7.49}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, is it the Government's position, Mr. Freidman, that even if the appellant maybe subjected successfully in England, or France, or both to a judgment for damages that that would not be a reason.","start":1158.848,"stop":1171.173,"duration":12.33},{"text":"The appellant should not do the same as now directed.","start":1171.173,"stop":1175.423,"duration":4.25}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No.","start":1175.423,"stop":1175.628,"duration":0.2},{"text":"We think that the -- the judgment does not require him to take steps which create a real likelihood of being subjected to judgment for pecuniary damages but I'd like to point out that that is, we think extremely conjectural.","start":1175.628,"stop":1192.731,"duration":17.1},{"text":"Mr. Stevens had spoken about this entry of appearance was a -- which is available.","start":1192.731,"stop":1197.854,"duration":5.12},{"text":"The entry of appearance however, was not made in the basic contract which was found illegal in this suit, the basic 1925 sharing agreement.","start":1197.854,"stop":1207.614,"duration":9.76},{"text":"The entry of appearance related only to the agreement to sell the business and subsequent agreements modifying the basic agreement.","start":1207.614,"stop":1215.981,"duration":8.37},{"text":"And I would assume that under these circumstances, the argument at least could be pressed by appellant before the English court that there is no entry of appearance.","start":1215.981,"stop":1225.975,"duration":9.99}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"But if you -- if they do what the decree requires them -- them to do, namely to do business in England, it bring themselves within the jurisdiction of the English courts.","start":1225.975,"stop":1237.933,"duration":11.96}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"If, Mr. Justice, the question of how they do business may well determine whether they have to go into the English court.","start":1237.933,"stop":1246.103,"duration":8.17},{"text":"They may find that they can effectively sell products in England without ever setting foot in England.","start":1246.103,"stop":1250.95,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, but -- but the English courts may follow this Court's decision, even one of Due Process Clause in the case like the Washington case as to what constitutes subservience to jurisdiction.","start":1250.95,"stop":1264.107,"duration":13.16}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"But -- once again, I would like to emphasize that --","start":1264.107,"stop":1270.717,"duration":6.61}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Friedman, I hope -- I hope you didn't suggest in that last answer that maybe they can do just enough things not to get caught by an English court, and that's all right.","start":1270.717,"stop":1279.899,"duration":9.18}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"No, I wasn't suggesting in that sense, certainly, Mr. Justice.","start":1279.899,"stop":1283.522,"duration":3.62},{"text":"I was suggesting that before they subjected to any real likelihood of being held liable here, we have to have -- we think there has to be something more than a mere statement that they are threatened with suit by one of these companies, a threat made at a time when the matter was pending before the District Court and which obviously was designed in attempt to influence the judgment of the District Court.","start":1283.522,"stop":1312.827,"duration":29.31},{"text":"They may -- we don't know the British company may well conclude that would see advertisements beginning to appear in British territory.","start":1312.827,"stop":1322.329,"duration":9.5},{"text":"It adheres that the American company is attempting -- getting business in England that they're better off to forget this territorial allocation.","start":1322.329,"stop":1330.259,"duration":7.93},{"text":"They may decide -- we've had enough of this cartel.","start":1330.259,"stop":1332.744,"duration":2.48},{"text":"We can undersell the American company, the American -- let the American company come in here.","start":1332.744,"stop":1337.362,"duration":4.62},{"text":"We'll go into America and we'll take over most of their market.","start":1337.362,"stop":1341.994,"duration":4.63},{"text":"That --","start":1341.994,"stop":1342.52,"duration":0.53}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"May I suggest that it doesn't comfort very well with the dignity of this country.","start":1342.52,"stop":1347.388,"duration":4.87},{"text":"And to me, it doesn't seem desirable in international relation to wait in the suit as broad and an English court says, “No, we don't have to respect or to threaten -- threaten (Inaudible) in an English court would allow the suit -- suit for damages, and then rush to Judge Underwood's court and say, (Inaudible) the English court as you restrict it, so let's change decree.","start":1347.388,"stop":1370.351,"duration":22.96},{"text":"I don't think that's a very dignified attitude for this country or for this -- for the judicial system of this country to take.","start":1370.351,"stop":1379.829,"duration":9.48}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Friedman, is there anything in that decree either so worded or by implication that would require this company to go over to England or any other foreign country and submit itself to the jurisdiction of that country as distinguished from holding itself out in this country as being willing to serve customers in any of those countries who might want to do business with it on -- on reasonable terms here under the jurisdiction of the United States.","start":1379.829,"stop":1417.204,"duration":37.38}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, in the -- Mr. Justice -- Chief Justice, in the first instance at least, we think that they can comply with it's judgment by staying in this country.","start":1417.204,"stop":1426.557,"duration":9.35},{"text":"Now, if it turns out that they merely hold themselves out.","start":1426.557,"stop":1432.09,"duration":5.53},{"text":"They put ads in and they wait here and they get no business, I suppose the question might well then arise whether they have complied with the provisions of the decree.","start":1432.09,"stop":1440.739,"duration":8.65},{"text":"I would suggest at that point, they may well go back to Judge Underwood and say, “This is what we've done, nothing has happened, isn't this reasonable effort?”","start":1440.739,"stop":1450.49,"duration":9.75},{"text":"And if the judge agrees in the point if he says no, then, it seems to me that is the time -- that point to challenge any of the further step, which the decree contemplates.","start":1450.49,"stop":1461.664,"duration":11.17}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Are you prepared, on behalf of the Government, to state whether you will accept the Chief Justice's rephrasing of what this decree does?","start":1461.664,"stop":1469.814,"duration":8.15},{"text":"Then they'd all have to do is to pull their arms here and say, we're willing to take any business that is solicited from us?","start":1469.814,"stop":1476.456,"duration":6.64}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, he didn't put it exactly that way.","start":1476.456,"stop":1478.678,"duration":2.22},{"text":"[Laughter]","start":1478.678,"stop":1479.731,"duration":1.05}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, on [Laughter] --","start":1479.731,"stop":1480.191,"duration":0.46}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"But that's the word --","start":1480.191,"stop":1481.539,"duration":1.35}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"-- Chief Justice were, will you substitute those -- that rephrasing for what is in this decree?","start":1481.539,"stop":1491.299,"duration":9.76},{"text":"After reflection, you think about it and then tell (Voice Overlap) --","start":1491.299,"stop":1493.103,"duration":1.8}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I'd -- I'd like to reflect upon it and --","start":1493.103,"stop":1495.017,"duration":1.91}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1495.017,"stop":1497.772,"duration":2.75}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"[Laughter]","start":1497.772,"stop":1498.356,"duration":0.58}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- and -- and then with -- with your kind permission, Mr. Justice, I would like if possible to consult with my superiors as to that but I don't I think I'm quite free to make this concession.","start":1498.356,"stop":1514.455,"duration":16.1},{"text":"I think that --","start":1514.455,"stop":1514.546,"duration":0.09}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I --","start":1514.546,"stop":1515.326,"duration":0.78}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I think the suggestion does go back a little from what the decree suggest and I think in all candid, I should say that I don't think I can read the decree in its present languages contemplating only that.","start":1515.326,"stop":1528.235,"duration":12.91},{"text":"On the other hand, we think that it is necessary that -- and we -- we believe it's very important that the -- a decree should be entered which goes beyond merely canceling the agreements.","start":1528.235,"stop":1539.011,"duration":10.78},{"text":"And if this Court naturally feels that the decree is presently -- and it goes too far, we certainly would have no objection for a modification along those --","start":1539.011,"stop":1545.528,"duration":6.52}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"You -- you -- would you agree -- would you agree that I can barely read the decree and say, “Free the -- an error of activity demanded from the appellant?”","start":1545.528,"stop":1556.884,"duration":11.36}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would say it does, Your Honor.","start":1556.884,"stop":1567.032,"duration":10.15}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Is there any doubt in the mind of the Government to -- you wouldn't and is a case and there's power to -- to repel activities, actual activities in foreign -- on foreign soil of these companies?","start":1567.032,"stop":1584.574,"duration":17.54}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we don't think there's any -- any question of power.","start":1584.574,"stop":1587.974,"duration":3.4},{"text":"We think the real issue here is whether the Court has gone beyond its proper discretion.","start":1587.974,"stop":1595.661,"duration":7.69},{"text":"Court of equity --","start":1595.661,"stop":1596.155,"duration":0.49}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"The equitable power is sufficiently great to -- so far as if they go to whatever point in the world may be necessary --","start":1596.155,"stop":1602.961,"duration":6.81}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we think so that --","start":1602.961,"stop":1603.964,"duration":1}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"-- to carry its activities.","start":1603.964,"stop":1605.245,"duration":1.28}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that a court of equity has the power to direct the defendant to take steps beyond its borders and --","start":1605.245,"stop":1611.929,"duration":6.68}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"But that's the general equity power and not power that flows from the Sherman Act?","start":1611.929,"stop":1618.917,"duration":6.99}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":1618.917,"stop":1619.525,"duration":0.61},{"text":"We think that Sherman Act court, as a court of equity has that power, plus the power in the Court of -- in the Sherman Act to take steps to restrain and prevent.","start":1619.525,"stop":1632.014,"duration":12.49}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Do you have any decision that it proves a decree in this form even in this country?","start":1632.014,"stop":1637.978,"duration":5.96}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"In a substantially similar provision, Mr. Justice Burton, was contained in the decree in the I.C.I. case.","start":1637.978,"stop":1645.798,"duration":7.82},{"text":"Not the aspect of it that was litigated in the British court but another provision, which we have set out in page 48 of our brief.","start":1645.798,"stop":1653.353,"duration":7.56},{"text":"And in addition to that, we have set out in a footnote that there's been several recent consent decrees in which provision is directing the -- the parties --","start":1653.353,"stop":1663.075,"duration":9.72}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"That on page 48, has that been judicially approved?","start":1663.075,"stop":1666.939,"duration":3.86}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That has not been reported but that is the paragraph as entered in the I.C.I. case.","start":1666.939,"stop":1672.789,"duration":5.85}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. -- Mr. Friedman, may I trouble to ask you whether the cases noted in the footnote, in your footnote 32.","start":1672.789,"stop":1681.619,"duration":8.83},{"text":"Will I find the terms of the decree and those citations or the Department says we must have to the -- if they're not to be had, they're not available in some publications.","start":1681.619,"stop":1694.771,"duration":13.15},{"text":"Would it be convenient for the Department to say the -- what this means to prior analogous decree?","start":1694.771,"stop":1701.863,"duration":7.09}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"We will be happy to, Mr. Justice.","start":1701.863,"stop":1703.342,"duration":1.48},{"text":"These particular citations do contain the text --","start":1703.342,"stop":1705.394,"duration":2.05}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"They do?","start":1705.394,"stop":1706.087,"duration":0.69},{"text":"All right.","start":1706.087,"stop":1706.233,"duration":0.15}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- of the decrees in those cases.","start":1706.233,"stop":1707.185,"duration":0.95}]},{"speakerName":"Felix Frankfurter","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":1707.185,"stop":1707.381,"duration":0.2},{"text":"I agree can agree.","start":1707.381,"stop":1709.509,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you take the DuPont and listed it here at page 48?","start":1709.509,"stop":1713.971,"duration":4.46}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Sir?","start":1713.971,"stop":1714.68,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"Did you (Inaudible)","start":1714.68,"stop":1734.52,"duration":19.84},{"text":"Would you be willing to take the DuPont language?","start":1734.52,"stop":1740.888,"duration":6.37}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the only difficulty I have would be sound business judgment concept, is the difficulty of determining what is sound business judgment.","start":1740.888,"stop":1760.727,"duration":19.84},{"text":"In other words, if this company should conclude that in its sound business judgment, it is not warranted in doing business in any of these countries, under the terms of the DuPont decree, I assume they're not required to go abroad.","start":1760.727,"stop":1780.176,"duration":19.45},{"text":"Now, sound business judgment, if it were in the sense that -- I -- I think to some extent at least, that is covered by the reasonable efforts provision.","start":1780.176,"stop":1792.34,"duration":12.16},{"text":"If it's something that just wouldn't make much sense from a business point of view at all.","start":1792.34,"stop":1797.215,"duration":4.88},{"text":"For example, to sell in a territory just not economically feasible because of the distance and because of the transportation difficulties, I think there is sound business judgment and reasonable efforts to coalesce.","start":1797.215,"stop":1810.047,"duration":12.83}]},{"speakerName":"William J. Brennan, Jr.","textObjs":[{"text":"Well now, don't you think there that reasonable efforts is more an objective test, whereas DuPont's sound business judgment is largely subject?","start":1810.047,"stop":1821.299,"duration":11.25}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I think so but I think that again, the two do coalesce because in determining what are reasonable efforts, you have to look to what is a sound business judgment.","start":1821.299,"stop":1836.114,"duration":14.82},{"text":"The thing -- to be quite frank that I'm afraid of under this provision, this would leave the way open for these people to reach the same result as they had in the past without the arrange -- benefit of this cartel arrangement.","start":1836.114,"stop":1849.944,"duration":13.83},{"text":"They would -- could well determine as a matter of a sound business judgment but they didn't want to go into these countries.","start":1849.944,"stop":1855.838,"duration":5.89},{"text":"Now, I think that --","start":1855.838,"stop":1857.755,"duration":1.92}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"DuPont can give no (Inaudible)","start":1857.755,"stop":1860.796,"duration":3.04}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe so, Mr. Justice.","start":1860.796,"stop":1863.861,"duration":3.07}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Friedman, may I ask this -- this question.","start":1863.861,"stop":1866.965,"duration":3.1},{"text":"What would you think of a combination of -- of the -- these two things.","start":1866.965,"stop":1872.562,"duration":5.6},{"text":"One, the portion of the decree requiring these advertising features in -- in other lands, plus this provision to make such efforts as unreasonable according to their sound business judgment.","start":1872.562,"stop":1887.224,"duration":14.66},{"text":"Now, would -- would that take care of the little you were talking about?","start":1887.224,"stop":1890.791,"duration":3.57}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think it would, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":1890.791,"stop":1895.607,"duration":4.82},{"text":"I might mention --","start":1895.607,"stop":1896.862,"duration":1.26}]},{"speakerName":"Tom C. Clark","textObjs":[{"text":"What's your position is -- is -- let me see if I understand it.","start":1896.862,"stop":1901.062,"duration":4.2},{"text":"Suppose the decree was to stand and the Government came in (Inaudible) in fact they haven't made any legal efforts.","start":1901.062,"stop":1910.655,"duration":9.59},{"text":"Then, would be the time for them to raise their -- and to introduce their evidence, proved that they have a legal reference, is that your position?","start":1910.655,"stop":1919.345,"duration":8.69},{"text":"And not now under this --","start":1919.345,"stop":1920.962,"duration":1.62}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"That is correct.","start":1920.962,"stop":1921.692,"duration":0.73},{"text":"With this further suggestion that if in the intervening period they determined that it just isn't feasible for them and they just can't carry this thing out, they can then go before the District Court.","start":1921.692,"stop":1939.652,"duration":17.96},{"text":"I think it's -- it's rather significant here that this company is -- indicates that it has no wish to try to sell abroad and yet quite significantly, it felt it was worth $40,000 to it to purchase the rights to do business in South America.","start":1939.652,"stop":1959.645,"duration":19.99},{"text":"So that when they say they have no desire to go abroad but we think it's pretty clear and it's also shown by the way in which they keep referring orders to these foreign companies unless the foreign company agrees.","start":1959.645,"stop":1974.317,"duration":14.67},{"text":"In situations where they get the consent of the foreign company, they have no hesitancy in shipping an order into the territory of that company.","start":1974.317,"stop":1982.722,"duration":8.4},{"text":"So that, we think it's pretty clear from this record that this company is staying out of these territories not because as a matter of business judgment.","start":1982.722,"stop":1992.944,"duration":10.22},{"text":"It doesn't think it wants to do business in these areas but rather because these agreements are bound to it to stay out and in turn, the other companies are giving it absence of competition in the domestic market.","start":1992.944,"stop":2007.494,"duration":14.55},{"text":"Now, we think, Mr. Chief Justice, that a combination of the giving them some measure of discretion in the exercise of business judgment where it's appropriate that they should not take certain steps in combination with these specific steps, would be a admirable solution to this -- what seems to be this dilemma or one hand, a need for something to be done and on the other hand, the problem of -- we -- we don't want to put them in the position where they feel they've got a club hanging over them that they -- we -- we're not suggesting they had to go abroad and get themselves subjected to serious damage suits.","start":2007.494,"stop":2051.882,"duration":44.39},{"text":"That they have to -- to do something which is basically more than is required under the circumstances of this case to dissipate these restraints on trade.","start":2051.882,"stop":2064.292,"duration":12.41}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Supposed they were charged with contempt as you suggested or was suggested to you.","start":2064.292,"stop":2069.203,"duration":4.91},{"text":"They came in and said, “We haven't been doing business (Inaudible) we've been advised that the contract is illegal over there, almost an illegal over here and subject ourselves to (Inaudible)","start":2069.203,"stop":2086.148,"duration":16.95},{"text":"They said as -- and that's the result before we can file with the decree in trying to get this.","start":2086.148,"stop":2091.791,"duration":5.64},{"text":"We file a proceeding in court over there to -- until the matter is adjudicated.","start":2091.791,"stop":2095.782,"duration":3.99},{"text":"Do you think that any court was doing things over for subpoena.","start":2095.782,"stop":2099.181,"duration":3.4}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"In England, you mean?","start":2099.181,"stop":2100.132,"duration":0.95}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"I mean here.","start":2100.132,"stop":2101.252,"duration":1.12}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Well, I would think --","start":2101.252,"stop":2101.658,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose you came up it that statement that they were worried about it, they thought was uneven.","start":2101.658,"stop":2106.989,"duration":5.33},{"text":"They'd gone over there and had filed a proceeding in order to get the matter adjudicated before they attempted to do business.","start":2106.989,"stop":2116.698,"duration":9.71},{"text":"Do you think that would be -- relieve them from punishment under the contempt --","start":2116.698,"stop":2121.332,"duration":4.63}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"In the -- in the --","start":2121.332,"stop":2121.882,"duration":0.55}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"-- charge?","start":2121.882,"stop":2122.777,"duration":0.89}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Justice, the --","start":2122.777,"stop":2123.918,"duration":1.14}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Would that be reasonable?","start":2123.918,"stop":2125.01,"duration":1.09},{"text":"Would that -- in other words, would that be reasonable?","start":2125.01,"stop":2126.615,"duration":1.6}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would think so.","start":2126.615,"stop":2127.766,"duration":1.15},{"text":"That if -- if they went to, as Mr. Justice Frankfurter had suggested --","start":2127.766,"stop":2130.821,"duration":3.05}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes.","start":2130.821,"stop":2131.231,"duration":0.41}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"-- earlier.","start":2131.231,"stop":2131.48,"duration":0.25},{"text":"If they went to an English court and sought a -- some sort of declaratory relief, I don't know whether the court would give it to them.","start":2131.48,"stop":2137.859,"duration":6.38},{"text":"But if they did and the court said no, we still would consider this agreement valid under English law.","start":2137.859,"stop":2143.083,"duration":5.22},{"text":"You attempt to do business in this country, you're going to get in trouble.","start":2143.083,"stop":2146.873,"duration":3.79},{"text":"I think that would constitute a showing of, having taken a reason --","start":2146.873,"stop":2149.757,"duration":2.88}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What I mean to -- suppose they -- suppose they had enacted what they were citing for contempt before the -- this got action.","start":2149.757,"stop":2156.195,"duration":6.44},{"text":"Would you consider that they were doing -- implying with the decree and the reason (Voice Overlap) --","start":2156.195,"stop":2159.209,"duration":3.01}]},{"speakerName":"Mr. Attorney General","textObjs":[{"text":"I would -- I would think they were using reasonable efforts if they attempted in good faith to try to ascertain or just what the consequences would be of the various competitive steps.","start":2159.209,"stop":2171.154,"duration":11.95},{"text":"And I want to emphasize once again that there's nothing in this decree which directs the appellant specifically to go abroad in the sense of sending personnel abroad, of sending goods abroad, of setting up warehouses, of taking any steps which may actually subject them to any damages.","start":2171.154,"stop":2195.618,"duration":24.46},{"text":"That at least as far as it appears in the first instance, we think all that is required under reasonable efforts is to stay right within the boarders of the United States and try to reach out and see to what extent they can stimulate this foreign commerce, and then to go forward from that point.","start":2195.618,"stop":2213.657,"duration":18.04},{"text":"Thank you.","start":2213.657,"stop":2217.541,"duration":3.88}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevenson -- Stevens, you may proceed.","start":2217.541,"stop":2221.769,"duration":4.23}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"If the Court please.","start":2221.769,"stop":2227.374,"duration":5.61},{"text":"It seems to me that the discussion of counsel for the Government has ignored one vital fact.","start":2227.374,"stop":2236.222,"duration":8.85},{"text":"That is that the record already shows in this case how this company deems it reasonable to conduct its business.","start":2236.222,"stop":2247.067,"duration":10.84},{"text":"And it is incontrovertible on the record that we deem it reasonable, in fact necessary in the conduct of our business to sell through skill-trained engineers.","start":2247.067,"stop":2262.274,"duration":15.21},{"text":"In other words, the product, the physical product of Holophane Company Inc. is sold 75% in conjunction with the engineering service which it renders.","start":2262.274,"stop":2277.48,"duration":15.21},{"text":"Indeed, engineering service, scientific lighting service is the chief product of Holophane Company.","start":2277.48,"stop":2287.668,"duration":10.19},{"text":"Therefore, to have on hand, even unmarked or newly marked glass to say nothing of the shadiness of circumvention implied in that resort.","start":2287.668,"stop":2304.863,"duration":17.19},{"text":"To have on hand that glass when the Government says, “You are not expected to send somebody abroad to sell it,” is imposing upon this small company a financial burden which it should not be required to assume.","start":2304.863,"stop":2322.48,"duration":17.62},{"text":"Because in order to have newly marked or unmarked glass, cutting right across its whole inventory, it must make an entirely new set of glass for expert -- export purposes and would be subjected to an irretrievable cost in doing that upon the theory that we are not expected to send somebody abroad.","start":2322.48,"stop":2349.097,"duration":26.62}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Does the record show that?","start":2349.097,"stop":2351.034,"duration":1.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"I believe it does, Your Honor.","start":2351.034,"stop":2353.007,"duration":1.97},{"text":"Now, I -- I --","start":2353.007,"stop":2353.664,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"(Voice Overlap) possibly into just explaining to us the --","start":2353.664,"stop":2357.064,"duration":3.4}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Now --","start":2357.064,"stop":2357.298,"duration":0.23}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"-- that manufacturing glass, which now is in molds and so forth --","start":2357.298,"stop":2361.487,"duration":4.19}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":2361.487,"stop":2362.073,"duration":0.59}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"You have to have both.","start":2362.073,"stop":2363.23,"duration":1.16}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":2363.23,"stop":2363.908,"duration":0.68}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Is that -- you don't know where that appears in the record, do you?","start":2363.908,"stop":2366.229,"duration":2.32}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"There is no extensive discussion of that in the record.","start":2366.229,"stop":2368.602,"duration":2.37},{"text":"I'm sure, Your Honor.","start":2368.602,"stop":2370.455,"duration":1.85},{"text":"It is in the record that we do so through the engineers, as I have said.","start":2370.455,"stop":2376.256,"duration":5.8}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, Mr. Stevens, do you -- assume that the Court finds that your contracts were illegal.","start":2376.256,"stop":2382.73,"duration":6.47},{"text":"Do you have any -- any great objection to doing the advertising things that this decree required, just the advertising?","start":2382.73,"stop":2391.672,"duration":8.94}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we do, Your Honor.","start":2391.672,"stop":2393.618,"duration":1.95}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Now, on what legal basis do you --","start":2393.618,"stop":2395.329,"duration":1.71}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"And we -- we say that --","start":2395.329,"stop":2396.322,"duration":0.99}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"-- object to that?","start":2396.322,"stop":2397.062,"duration":0.74}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"We say that the District Court has no right to order this defendant to take any affirmative steps in England or in France, or in foreign territories.","start":2397.062,"stop":2417.654,"duration":20.59},{"text":"We say that it is the responsibility of the Government in this case when it asks for relief, which may impinge upon the sovereignty of another country to have shown to the District Court that there would be no impingement in the type of order which it has sought and presented to the Court.","start":2417.654,"stop":2445.846,"duration":28.19},{"text":"We say that the specific requirement of advertising, even though a less tangible impingement upon the sovereignty of another nation is such an impingement because it is a thrusting into the territory of another country of activities by the sole defendant in an American case of conduct contrary to the law of those countries.","start":2445.846,"stop":2479.578,"duration":33.73},{"text":"And we say that it is a violation of international law so to do, and if it were not a violation of international law, if it were not in conflict with the law of England or the law of France, the burden on that matter rested with the Government and they should have carried the bar.","start":2479.578,"stop":2501.053,"duration":21.47},{"text":"They did not do it.","start":2501.053,"stop":2502.826,"duration":1.77}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"But what -- what provision of international law or what principle of international law does it violate for American company to say, “We will sell our product in every part of the world.","start":2502.826,"stop":2518.932,"duration":16.11},{"text":"We will sell it -- we're willing to sell it in England, or France, or Germany, or wherever -- wherever people -- wherever there might be customers, we our willing to sell to them.”","start":2518.932,"stop":2529.938,"duration":11.01},{"text":"Now, what --","start":2529.938,"stop":2530.869,"duration":0.93}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Starting de novo, Mr. Chief Justice.","start":2530.869,"stop":2534.742,"duration":3.87},{"text":"There would be no interference.","start":2534.742,"stop":2537.359,"duration":2.62}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"What?","start":2537.359,"stop":2537.641,"duration":0.28}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"But starting with the situation which we have in this case where there are contractual agreements binding upon limited in Francaise.","start":2537.641,"stop":2552.317,"duration":14.68},{"text":"And obviously and inherently untouched by any decree, unilaterally entered by Judge Underwood.","start":2552.317,"stop":2561.497,"duration":9.18},{"text":"We say that to require us to advertise is only a somewhat more subtle way of directing us to conduct our business affirmatively in that territory.","start":2561.497,"stop":2576.432,"duration":14.93},{"text":"In other words, we are no less violating the contractual rights of -- limited in Francaise by advertising and saying that Barcus is willing from these shores.","start":2576.432,"stop":2589.212,"duration":12.78},{"text":"Then we are -- if we send our men abroad, assuming we could find them and train them to sell the product in the only way we really know how to sell it.","start":2589.212,"stop":2600.917,"duration":11.7}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What practical objections do you have and -- and do the record show that you have in a business way to advertising if you could actually get customers over there.","start":2600.917,"stop":2612.308,"duration":11.39},{"text":"I'm not talking about your contract now, which suffice your concern in this country is illegal.","start":2612.308,"stop":2617.157,"duration":4.85}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the --","start":2617.157,"stop":2617.264,"duration":0.11}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"But what practice is --","start":2617.264,"stop":2617.921,"duration":0.66}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"The -- the practical objection, Your Honor, would be that our business experience is that 75% of this product is sold in conjunction with the engineering services, which we render.","start":2617.921,"stop":2633.683,"duration":15.76},{"text":"And that we would be sitting in this country when they cross the Board's inventory, designed to meet the requirements of this decree in newly marked or unmarked glass.","start":2633.683,"stop":2647.093,"duration":13.41},{"text":"And would at most achieve a 25% result on the inventory which we could have if we in fact sold.","start":2647.093,"stop":2658.051,"duration":10.96}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Suppose you could sell 25% more.","start":2658.051,"stop":2660.064,"duration":2.01},{"text":"I guess you're in business to sell though --","start":2660.064,"stop":2661.994,"duration":1.93}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Right.","start":2661.994,"stop":2662.199,"duration":0.2}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"That's what I don't understand.","start":2662.199,"stop":2663.102,"duration":0.9}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"We -- we are -- but if -- what I am saying is that in order to sell that 25%, we would be subjected to the penalty of making an entirely new inventory of glass, unmarked or newly marked for sale in the territories of limited in Francaise.","start":2663.102,"stop":2683.638,"duration":20.54},{"text":"In other words, the regular Holophane inventory of glass with the Holophane trademark on it cannot be sold abroad.","start":2683.638,"stop":2694.412,"duration":10.77}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the glass would be the same glass, wouldn't it?","start":2694.412,"stop":2696.176,"duration":1.76}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"It would be the same glass but it would have to be cast in new molds in order to have it without mark or bearing a new mark.","start":2696.176,"stop":2703.49,"duration":7.31}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"What you're saying now is that -- as I gather, that the practical business objection you would have under those circumstances would be that the culture would be more than the profits you can get from the business.","start":2703.49,"stop":2713.624,"duration":10.13}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"That's correct.","start":2713.624,"stop":2714.486,"duration":0.86},{"text":"There would be a penalty inflicted upon us.","start":2714.486,"stop":2717.378,"duration":2.89}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Mr. Stevens, in answering the Chief Justice, you rested your case on this being active as abroad.","start":2717.378,"stop":2723.783,"duration":6.4},{"text":"What is your position as to this kind of a decree to -- limited to this country?","start":2723.783,"stop":2728.81,"duration":5.03},{"text":"Is there any precedent for making this kind of an affirmative decree here?","start":2728.81,"stop":2732.915,"duration":4.11}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"I know of none.","start":2732.915,"stop":2734.503,"duration":1.59},{"text":"I know of none and I think that -- I think that the suggestion that -- that the DuPont decree, the I.C.I. DuPont decree is comparable, is wholly beside the point because that inserted an entirely subjective test.","start":2734.503,"stop":2751.798,"duration":17.29},{"text":"That is DuPont in -- in the exercise of its business judgment.","start":2751.798,"stop":2756.508,"duration":4.71},{"text":"There is no such provision here.","start":2756.508,"stop":2759.248,"duration":2.74}]},{"speakerName":"Harold Burton","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, what is your legal objection to a provision such as they put in the DuPont case, the one on page 48 of the Government's brief, that's the one providing that they make such efforts that are reasonable according to DuPont sound business judgment, not arrived at and not influenced by unlawful motives or purposes.","start":2759.248,"stop":2779.476,"duration":20.23}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, the legal objection, Your Honor, is back on the point of a violation of international law.","start":2779.476,"stop":2787.021,"duration":7.55},{"text":"That is, that such an order, even with a subjective test, impinges upon the sovereignty of other nations.","start":2787.021,"stop":2797.959,"duration":10.94},{"text":"And that whether we like or not, as a matter of jurisdiction, it just doesn't exist.","start":2797.959,"stop":2804.447,"duration":6.49}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Have you quoted such cases in your brief?","start":2804.447,"stop":2806.578,"duration":2.13}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"We have quoted authorities which we believe support that point.","start":2806.578,"stop":2810.462,"duration":3.88}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Where are they found?","start":2810.462,"stop":2813.467,"duration":3.01}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"In the -- the appellants brief, Your Honor.","start":2813.467,"stop":2825.061,"duration":11.59},{"text":"Those cases are found, beginning at page 36, I believe.","start":2825.061,"stop":2836.245,"duration":11.18},{"text":"We say that the Banana case indicated that the Sherman Act applies within this country, as recently as Steele v. Bulova Watch, it was so cited.","start":2836.245,"stop":2857.465,"duration":21.22},{"text":"And we say that this country simply cannot impose its antitrust laws and its concept there under upon foreign countries.","start":2857.465,"stop":2867.342,"duration":9.88}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, it did -- it did that exercise some extra territorial authority, did they not in the Bulova Watch case?","start":2867.342,"stop":2873.677,"duration":6.34}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"Yes, and that is most interesting because in the exercise of that, if Your Honor will look at the footnote 17 in which Imperial Chemicals and the British Nylon Spinners litigation is cited, is made perfectly clear that it was when as in this case, there is no interference for the sovereignty of another nation.","start":2873.677,"stop":2905.243,"duration":31.57},{"text":"And that case, Your Honor, was decided in this Court after the Supreme Court of Mexico had set aside the registration of the Bulova trademark by the defendant in that case in Mexico.","start":2905.243,"stop":2922.995,"duration":17.75},{"text":"And so, it was approached with the Mexican law being in complete accord with our law and therefore, no infringement upon its sovereignty.","start":2922.995,"stop":2933.142,"duration":10.15}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I understand you to explain as the Banana case held that the constitution of the United States forbids this country if it wants to, to sell its goods anywhere it can?","start":2933.142,"stop":2945.724,"duration":12.58}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"I did not, sir.","start":2945.724,"stop":2946.709,"duration":0.98},{"text":"No, sir.","start":2946.709,"stop":2947.185,"duration":0.48}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I -- I understood you --","start":2947.185,"stop":2947.891,"duration":0.71}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"No, no.","start":2947.891,"stop":2948.802,"duration":0.91},{"text":"I -- I said that the Banana case, as I have read it and as was cited as recently as Steele v. Bulova says that the Sherman Act --","start":2948.802,"stop":2960.084,"duration":11.28}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Oh, yes.","start":2960.084,"stop":2960.296,"duration":0.21}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"-- applies to Acts within this country.","start":2960.296,"stop":2962.4,"duration":2.1}]},{"speakerName":"Hugo L. Black","textObjs":[{"text":"Well, I understood that.","start":2962.4,"stop":2963.982,"duration":1.58}]},{"speakerName":"Richard F. Stevens","textObjs":[{"text":"That is a territorial record.","start":2963.982,"stop":2966.122,"duration":2.14}]},{"speakerName":"Earl Warren","textObjs":[{"text":"Thank you.","start":2966.122,"stop":2973.925,"duration":7.8}]}]}],"decidedBy":"Warren Court","arguedOn":"Nov 5, 1956","petitioner":"","respondent":"","docket":"2","citation":"352 US 903 (1956)","justiaLink":"https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/352/903","lowerCourt":"","grantedOn":"","decidedOn":"Nov 13, 1956"}